utor to learn more about starting a career in crafting.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4656,'If I Had a Hammer','Tradeskill','Unknown',5,5,'The local mender has offered to show me how to use some of the harvests I gathered to craft a small lucky charm using his anvil.',0,'I spoke to the tradeskill tutor to learn more about starting a career in crafting.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4657,'If I Had A Hammer','Tradeskill','Unknown',5,5,'The local mender has offered to show me how to use some of the harvests I gathered to craft a small lucky charm using his anvil.',0,'I spoke to the tradeskill tutor to learn more about starting a career in crafting.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4658,'If I Had A Hammer','Tradeskill','Unknown',5,5,'The local mender has offered to show me how to use some of the harvests I gathered to craft a small lucky charm using his anvil.',0,'I spoke to the tradeskill tutor to learn more about starting a career in crafting.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4659,'If I Had A Hammer','Tradeskill','Unknown',5,5,'The local mender has offered to show me how to use some of the harvests I gathered to craft a small lucky charm using his anvil.',0,'I spoke to the tradeskill tutor to learn more about starting a career in crafting.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4660,'If I Had A Hammer','Tradeskill','Unknown',5,5,'The local mender has offered to show me how to use some of the harvests I gathered to craft a small lucky charm using his anvil. Should I need to return to Oakmyst Forest, I may do so via any mariner bell within the City of Qeynos.',0,'I spoke to the tradeskill tutor to learn more about starting a career in crafting.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4661,'Shipwrecked!','Tradeskill','Unknown',5,5,'I received a mysterious message in a bottle which was apparently found washed up from the ocean nearby. I\'d better take this home and investigate what it says.',0,'A spell on a message in a bottle took me to an abandoned isle and the remains of a shipwreck. The only survivor I could find was a young ratonga boy named Raffik, who was on his way to Freeport with his parents to train as a fury. I revived him and left him to finish recovering.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4662,'Tutorial: Learning to Cook','Tradeskill','Unknown',5,5,'The tradeskill tutor has asked me to try my hand at provisioning.',0,'I created the jum jum cider as instructed by the tutor.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4663,'Tutorial: The Art of Weapons','Tradeskill','Unknown',6,6,'The tradeskill tutor has asked me to try my hand at making weapons.',0,'I created the weapons as instructed by the tutor.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4664,'Tutorial: Scribing Scrolls','Tradeskill','Unknown',7,7,'The tradeskill tutor has asked me to try my hand at sagecraft.',0,'I created the scroll as instructed by the tutor.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4665,'Tutorial: Alchemical Experiments','Tradeskill','Unknown',8,8,'The tradeskill tutor has asked me to try my hand at alchemy.',0,'I created the essence as instructed by the tutor.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4666,'Tutorial: Essential Outfitting','Tradeskill','Unknown',9,9,'The tradeskill tutor has asked me to try my hand at tailoring and armorsmithing.',0,'I created the backpack and chainmail coat as instructed by the tutor.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4667,'Castaway','Tradeskill','Unknown',10,10,'The harbormaster sent me a message that another bottle had washed ashore from the same direction I arrived from recently in the old rowboat. He read the note this time and says someone called Raffik is asking for my urgent help. I\'d better see if the spell on that old message in a bottle still works.',0,'Raffik was a little annoyed that I\'d taken the only rowboat when I left last time. When he finished gathering up his parents\' recipes from the wreckage, he found he had no way to leave! Fortunately he was able to get me another message, and when I returned I cooked him up some food and used his parents\' recipe to make a teleportation spell that could take us both home','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4668,'Piratical Fashion','Tradeskill','Unknown',20,20,'Raffik sent me a message to say he\'s safely back on the mainland but decided he doesn\'t like Freeport, and plans to become a pirate instead of a fury. He\'s still looking for his parents and asked if I would meet him in the Butcherblock Mountains.',0,'I found young Raffik in the Butcherblock Mountains trying to find &quot;shinies&quot; on the beach. He explained he\'s decided to become a pirate so he can get his own boat and look for his parents more easily. In the mean time, he asked my help to make him some new piratical style clothes instead of the shipwrecked rags he was still wearing. I talked to one of the fae tailors and made him a nice new outfit that he says he\'ll try on after &quot;just one more shinie&quot;. In return, he gave me one of his parents\' salvaged recipes for an option which will help the user gather collectibles faster and increase the chance of a bountiful harvest on normal harvesting','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4669,'Adorning the Pirate','Tradeskill','Unknown',30,30,'I got another message from Raffik saying everyone admires his new outfit very much, and can I help him make a piratical sword?',0,'I met Raffik once again in the Butcherblock Mountains. The local mender was helping him to repair an old sword he found on the beach, and he asked me to talk to the local transmuting merchant about getting a nice piratical adornment to improve it. The local merchant was happy to help the poor boy, so I made him the adornment. In return, Raffik gave me one of his parents\' recipes for a potion that improves the user\'s chances of getting rare components when transmuting','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4670,'Encompassing Goal','Tradeskill','Unknown',40,40,'Raffik has somehow gotten lost and is apparently near Klak\'anon in the Steamfont Mountains. He said something about needing a compass, and asked if I can help.',0,'Raffik had learned that the clockwork salvagers in Steamfont contain a compass device, but the delicate mechanism is too easily broken to be obtained by combat. I helped him find a device that would stun the clockwork salvagers so I could gently remove the compass, and brought it to Raffik for his future piratical navigation.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4671,'Halasians for Hire','Tradeskill','Unknown',50,50,'I received another note from young Raffik, who is apparently now in New Halas trying to hire a pirate crew. He says he would like my help if I\'m in the area.',0,'I met Raffik in New Halas, where he was attempting to hire mercenaries. He said his parents had a recipe that would improve the efficiency of mercenaries, and since I am an excellent crafter, he wanted to know if I would make it for him. In exchange, I would be welcome to keep a copy of the recipe for my own use. Seemed like a good deal to me.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4672,'Halasian Hangover','Tradeskill','Unknown',60,60,'I got a strange letter from one of the night guards in New Halas. He said &quot;my friend&quot; might appreciate some help in the Ravens\' Roost tavern. This sounds worrying...',0,'Apparently the letter was referring to my young friend Raffik, who had unwisely decided to try the local apple rum with his new mercenary pals. I obtained a hangover cure from the coldain bartender and brewed it up for Raffik, who has seen the error of his ways. As a bonus, the hangover cure also appears to cure resurrection sickness, headaches, and hiccups, so this could be useful.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4673,'Hired Scales','Tradeskill','Unknown',70,70,'I received another note from Raffik, who has apparently been searching for his parents around Kunark and is now in Teren\'s Grasp. He mentioned some trouble with his hired assistant and asked if I would have time to assist again.',0,'Raffik had already hired a local iksar to help train his mercenary friend in the art of combat, but I also spoke to the tutor and obtained the recipe for a charm that the iksar tutors use to help young students. The student uses it before battle starts and it helps them taunt better, or avoid the enemy\'s attention, as appropriate. This recipe may be useful for me, also','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4674,'Air Fare','Tradeskill','Unknown',80,80,'Another note from my young friend Raffik has arrived, asking if I have time to assist him in Paineel, in the Sundered Frontier. If interested, I should meet him there.',0,'On seeing the erudites\' flying transports, Raffik was apparently struck by the desire to have not just a pirate ship, but a flying pirate ship. He persuaded me to make a valuable potion of his parents\' and try to trade it with the erudites for a flying ship. Unfortunately the erudites insisted this was not possible. I left Raffik contemplating flying pirate ship alternatives. I did get a useful recipe from the deal though, for a potion which improves the results of refining','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4675,'Flying Feathers','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Another note from Raffik, this time apparently from Velious. After his flying pirate ship enquiries in Paineel, I can only guess he\'s trying to convince gryphons to tow a pirate ship or something ... but he has asked me to meet him at the Rookery in the Great Divide when I have time.',0,'My guess that Raffik was still thinking about flying pirate ships wasn\'t far wrong. He was busy interrogating the goahmari, and asked me to check the library in Thurgadin to see if they had any research on gryphons that might allow them to carry a whole crew or people instead of just one. I did find one interesting potion that seems to increase the speed of a mount of any type, but nothing that would help Raffik\'s goal unfortunately. I tried to suggest he might want to settle for a regular water-based ship like the Far Seas traders use, but I\'m not sure if he was convinced','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4676,'On A Boat','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'A note arrived from Raffik today. He sounds very excited and says he\'s on a boat in the Isle of Mara. Since my dealings with the young ratonga seem to be surprisingly profitable, I\'ll go see what he wants when I have a moment.',0,'Somewhat to my surprise, Raffik did take my advice in Velious and gave up the idea of flying. After I put him in contact with the Far Seas traders, they have taken a liking to him and Captain Ingrid has even given him his own small boat to practice in. I helped Raffik to make some of her favorite brew as a thank you. Who knows, perhaps with a bit more experience Raffik will grow up to be one of the Far Seas Trading Company captains. If anything will ever let him find his parents, or proof they didn\'t survive the wreck, that might just do it','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4677,'Pirates!','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I happened to be exploring Obulus Frontier with Raffik, and came across some pirates near a beach. Raffik insists we should try talking to them, in case they\'ve seen or heard news of his parents.',0,'The iksar pirates we met weren\'t exactly helpful, but it turned out they DID know where Raffik\'s parents were! I was able to free them from the pirates and they were overjoyed to be reunited with Raffik, and happy to hear how well he\'s doing on his own','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4678,'Introduction to the Ravens','Tradeskill','Frostfang Sea',15,0,'Tami Swifthammer has been sent from the Ironforge Exchange in Qeynos to offer help to New Halas. She has been assisting in establishing the new settlement and has plenty of work to offer to crafters willing to lend a hand. To start, she has asked me to deliver a letter of introduction.',4700293,'I delivered Tami\'s introduction letter to the leader of the Ravens of the North, and returned his thanks to her','Quests/FrostfangSea/IntroductiontotheRavens.lua'),(4679,'Fast Fabrication','Tradeskill','Frostfang Sea',15,0,'Tami said that when she returned from delivering the plates to the banquet hall, she discovered that the rolls of fabric in the shop had been badly damaged. Once again, it happened at a time when everyone was distracted, and saw nothing. She has asked me if I have time to help create some new fabric, so the tailors of New Halas don\'t run short.',0,'The spare rolls of fabric in Erronson\'s Furs and Leathers shop had been mysteriously damaged. At Tami\'s suggestion, I did my best to craft some new rolls of fabric to replace the damaged ones so the tailors of New Halas would not run short, and she complimented my efforts','Quests/FrostfangSea/FastFabrication.lua'),(4680,'Let The Spinning Wheel Spin','Tradeskill','Frostfang Sea',15,0,'Tami returned from delivering cookies to discover that the spinning wheels in Erronson\'s shop were mysteriously broken. She asked me if I could make some new ones.',0,'I assisted Tami and the weavers of New Halas by making some new spinning wheels.','Quests/FrostfangSea/LetTheSpinningWheelSpin.lua'),(4681,'Party Plates','Tradeskill','Frostfang Sea',15,0,'While delivering cookies, I learned there was a shortage of plates for the upcoming banquet. Tami suggested that I could help to craft up a stack more so there will be enough plates.',0,'I used Tami\'s recipe to make a stack of spare plates for the upcoming banquet in New Halas','Quests/FrostfangSea/PartyPlates.lua'),(4682,'Picking Up On Local News','Tradeskill','Unknown',15,15,'Tami, in typical halfling manner, suggested that offering fresh cookies around town would be an excellent way to get to know people. We will both take a batch of cookies and see what news we pick up along the way.',0,'Tami and I delivered fresh baked cookies to a number of people around New Halas, and learned their names and local news.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4683,'Premonitions of Disaster','Tradeskill','Frostfang Sea',15,0,'Tami is concerned that all the little problems around New Halas add up into one big problem of sabotage, and that the statue of Erollisi may be the next target. She has asked me to help warn the local citizens to be alert for trouble.',0,'I warned the Sisters of Erollisi and the Wolves of the North of the possibility that someone might attempt to damage the Cairn of the Huntress. Thanks to our efforts, a would-be saboteur was prevented from damaging the statue. Let\'s hope this ends the mysterious problems that New Halas has been having lately!','Quests/FrostfangSea/PremonitionsofDisaster.lua'),(4684,'Rattled by Rats','Tradeskill','Frostfang Sea',15,0,'Tami suggested that I could help the Hopsons by making a simple rat trap for their home. Whether or not it ever catches any rats, it may calm their son\'s fears.',0,'I assisted Tami by creating a rat trap and placing it in the Hopsons\' abode to calm the fears of their son Tad','Quests/FrostfangSea/RattledbyRats.lua'),(4685,'Restocking the Cookie Jar','Tradeskill','Frostfang Sea',15,0,'Tami Swifthammer has asked if I can gather some local foodstuffs to restock her cooking supplies while she is busy baking up a fresh batch of cookies.',0,'I assisted Tami Swifthammer from the Ironforge Exchange by gathering local food harvests to refill her cooking supplies.','Quests/FrostfangSea/RestockingtheCookieJar.lua'),(4686,'Storage Situation','Tradeskill','Frostfang Sea',15,0,'When I returned to Tami, she mentioned that one of the merchants had reported a suspicious noise coming from the storehouse nearby. She asked me to run over and investigate.',0,'I investigated the Storage and Containment storehouse and discovered a fire in progress! Thinking quickly, I used a bucket of snow to extinguish the blaze, and returned to warn Tami.','Quests/FrostfangSea/StorageSituation.lua'),(4687,'Demands to the Ravens','Tradeskill','Unknown',15,15,'Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran has come from the Coalition of Tradesfolke in Freeport to persuade the residents of New Halas that an exclusive trading agreement with the Coalition is a deal they don\'t want to refuse. She needs someone to deliver her letter of demands to the Ravens of the North.',0,'I assisted Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran from the Coalition of Tradesfolke by delivering her letter of demands to Nikolas MacCraifft of the Ravens of the North faction. Unfortunately, I had to inform her that the Ravens of the North refused an exclusive trade deal','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4688,'A Dry Goods Run','Tradeskill','Unknown',15,15,'Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran has learned that the Ironforge Exchange and allied crafters have been working for New Halas for free, undermining her efforts to establish a trade monopoly. She has determined that the citizens of New Halas need to be taught a lesson ... and that I will assist her.',0,'I created a keg of explosive powder from the recipe that Commissioner Varla gave me, and tested it in the New Halas storehouse, with spectacularly explosive results.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4689,'A Little Friendly Sabotage','Tradeskill','Unknown',15,15,'Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran feels the Coalition could sell large quantities of finely spun wool to New Halas, if they weren\'t so efficient at making it themselves. She has suggested that I ensure their spinning wheels meet with an accident so that they will no longer be able to supply their own wool.',0,'I assisted Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran by damaging the spinning wheels in the city of New Halas, in hopes that the Coalition of Tradesfolke will profit from supplying the new demand for wool that they can no longer supply themselves','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4690,'Be Prepared','Tradeskill','Unknown',15,15,'Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran has asked me to familiarize myself with the area by gathering some harvests for the upcoming work I will be doing.',0,'I familiarized myself with the area around New Halas while gathering some of the local harvests I will require if I am to continue helping Varla.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4691,'Hit \'Em Where It Hurts','Tradeskill','Unknown',15,15,'Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran wishes to teach a final lesson to the citizens of New Halas by blowing up the shrine to Erollisi Marr that they hold so dear. She has instructed me to make more of the explosive kegs, and set them off in the Cairn of the Huntress.',0,'I attempted to destroy the Cairn of the Huntress using the explosive kegs that Varla taught me to make, but unfortunately, the guards were waiting in ambush and Varla and I were captured. Fortunately, Varla had a few tricks up her sleeve and was able to disable the guards so we could escape before I was questioned. She plans to make her way to Neriak to start her new career as a recipe salesman, and I think I have had enough attempted sabotage for now.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4692,'Market Shortages','Tradeskill','Unknown',15,15,'Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran is impatient that the residents of New Halas have not yet approached her about purchasing more wool, and suggested that perhaps if the fabric they make from it were damaged also, they would have no choice but to approach her soon. She has a recipe for an acid that specifically harms woolen fabric and has asked me to make some.',0,'I used the recipe Varla gave me to create a nasty vial of acid, which I then used on the rolls of fabric in Erronson\'s Furs and Leathers shop while Varla provided a distraction to empty the building. The fabric was ruined, and Varla should now be able to fill the demand with Coalition-produced cloth','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4693,'Ratting Them Out','Tradeskill','Unknown',15,15,'Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran has managed to obtain some genuine Ykeshan swamp rats, and would like them delivered discreetly to the Hopson abode in New Halas. Varla hopes this may discourage the Hopsons from promoting undesirable things such as Marr worship and free trade, and encourage them to end their pilgrimage and go home.',0,'At Varla\'s request, I discreetly dropped some Ykeshan swamp rats in the Hopson family\'s home in New Halas. She hopes that once the rats make their presence known, the Hopsons may be encouraged to leave New Halas and take their Marr worshipping, free-trade-promoting opinions with them.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4694,'Superior Spears','Tradeskill','Unknown',15,15,'Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran has a plan in mind, and needs my help to complete it. She has asked me to supply her with a number of unmarked spears and shields, and clearly has something specific in mind to do with them...',0,'I assisted Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran from the Coalition of Tradesfolke by making some spears for the Ry\'Gorr orcs, and some sturdy shields to sell to the New Halasians to defend against the orcs with the new, improved spears.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4695,'Supply and Demand','Tradeskill','Unknown',15,15,'Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran has heard there\'s an upcoming banquet planned, and suggested that the stores of spare plates in the city\'s storehouse might meet with an unfortunate accident before then. Happily, the Coalition has plenty of spare plates for sale, should they be needed.',0,'I assisted Commissioner Varla Z\'Velran by breaking the spare plates in the store room, so that the New Halas will need to purchase more before their upcoming banquet.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4696,'Journeyman Service','Tradeskill','Unknown',20,20,'My crafting society requires assistance in filling a large number of orders. I have offered to help with some journeyman rank tasks.Â ',0,'I have completed the journeyman rank task. The Grandmaster allowed me to choose an advanced book as my reward.Â ','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4697,'Tradesman Service','Tradeskill','Unknown',35,35,'My crafting society is concerned by rumours of a new strain of Kunarkian termites with a taste for briarwood lumber. They are concerned the termites might have migrated to Zek and the Enchanted Lands, and have asked me to sample some briarwood from those areas and run tests for the presence of the termites.Â ',0,'I tested briarwood from Zek and the Enchanted Lands for the presence of Kunarkian termites. Fortunately, it does not appear that the Kunarkian termites have reached these areas yet.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4698,'Advanced Alchemist Service','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'The Grandmaster has asked me to travel out to the shattered lands and bring supplies to a number of the society\'s surveyor contacts. I am also to collect their latest reports while I\'m there, and bring them back.',0,'I delivered the supplies to the surveyors, and brought their reports back to the Grandmaster.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4699,'Advanced Armorer Service','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'The Grandmaster has asked me to travel out to the shattered lands and bring supplies to a number of the society\'s surveyor contacts. I am also to collect their latest reports while I\'m there, and bring them back.',0,'I delivered the supplies to the surveyors, and brought their reports back to the Grandmaster.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4700,'Advanced Carpenter Service','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'The Grandmaster has asked me to travel out to the shattered lands and bring supplies to a number of the society\'s surveyor contacts. I am also to collect their latest reports while I\'m there, and bring them back.',0,'I delivered the supplies to the surveyors, and brought their reports back to the Grandmaster.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4701,'Advanced Jeweler Service','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'The Grandmaster has asked me to travel out to the Shattered Lands and bring supplies to a number of the society\'s surveyor contacts. I am also to collect their latest reports while I\'m there, and bring them back.',0,'I delivered the supplies to the surveyors, and brought their reports back to the Grandmaster.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4702,'Advanced Provisioner Service','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'The Grandmaster has asked me to travel out to the shattered lands and bring supplies to a number of the society\'s surveyor contacts. I am also to collect their latest reports while I\'m there, and bring them back.',0,'I delivered the supplies to the surveyors, and brought their reports back to the Grandmaster.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4703,'Advanced Sage Service','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'The Grandmaster has asked me to travel out to the shattered lands and bring supplies to a number of the society\'s surveyor contacts. I am also to collect their latest reports while I\'m there, and bring them back.',0,'I delivered the supplies to the surveyors, and brought their reports back to the Grandmaster.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4704,'Advanced Tailor Service','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'The Grandmaster has asked me to travel out to the shattered lands and bring supplies to a number of the society\'s surveyor contacts. I am also to collect their latest reports while I\'m there, and bring them back.',0,'I delivered the supplies to the surveyors, and brought their reports back to the Grandmaster.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4705,'Advanced Weaponsmith Service','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'The Grandmaster has asked me to travel out to the shattered lands and bring supplies to a number of the society\'s surveyor contacts. I am also to collect their latest reports while I\'m there, and bring them back.',0,'I delivered the supplies to the surveyors, and brought their reports back to the Grandmaster.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4706,'Advanced Woodworker Service','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'The Grandmaster has asked me to travel out to the shattered lands and bring supplies to a number of the society\'s surveyor contacts. I am also to collect their latest reports while I\'m there, and bring them back.',0,'I delivered the supplies to the surveyors, and brought their reports back to the Grandmaster.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4707,'Advanced Journeyman Tasks','Tradeskill','Unknown',55,55,'I have been sent to find a missing trading liaison who may be in need of assistance. I\'m no expert in these things, but I\'ll do my best to help.',0,'Fortunately the trading liaison seems to have survived... though I\'m not sure if I can take credit for that.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4708,'Senior Crafter Service','Tradeskill','Unknown',60,60,'The grandmaster has asked me to assist my tradeskill society once again, and seek out news of a harvesting team that was sent to gather tailoring supplies from the Overrealm.',0,'I located and assisted the missing harvesting team, and brought back some emergency supplies to keep the society\'s artisans working until the team can return with more.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4709,'A Binding Contract','Tradeskill','Unknown',25,25,'Cordelia Galeston, a Far Seas Trading Company representative, has offered me work and coin payment in exchange for my assistance to the Company in the Butcherblock Mountains. She has asked me to help by repairing a traveler\'s damaged tome that was recently damaged by aquagoblins.',0,'I assisted Cordelia by repairing the traveler\'s damaged tome that Dockmaster Waulon needed help restoring.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4710,'Alternate Assayer','Tradeskill','Unknown',25,25,'Bartleby explained that the Far Seas Trading Company hopes to trade with the Irontoe dwarves for the fine ore from the Mortartoe Mines, but he needs to confirm the quality of the ore meets Far Seas standards before the trade details can be agreed. He has asked me to gather ore samples and quality reports from the mine foremen to ascertain the grade of ore found within the Mortartoe Mine.',0,'I assisted Bartleby by gathering ore samples from the Mortartoe Mine and obtaining a copy of a recent ore quality report. Once he can confirm the ore quality is up to Far Seas standards, he will be able to proceed with trade negotiations with the Irontoe Brigade which should be of benefit to both.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4711,'Dwarven Blades','Tradeskill','Unknown',25,25,'Cordelia thanked me for my work for the Far Seas Trading Company, and requested that I travel to West Fort Irontoe where her colleague, Bartleby Blatherback, is in need of some assistance.',0,'I assisted Bartleby from the Far Seas Trading Company by gathering lost weapons in the area outside West Fort Irontoe. Now the weapons are safely in his hands where there\'s no risk that enemies of the fort might use them, he will be able to either repair or melt down the weapons for future profit.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4712,'For the Greater Goods','Tradeskill','Unknown',25,25,'Cordelia has urgently requested my help to make some protective spell scrolls for the Highland Outpost above the dock, which is under attack by kobolds.',0,'I assisted Cordelia Galeston and the local dwarves by crafting more protective spell scrolls to help defend the Highland Outpost from the recent kobold attacks.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4713,'Freelance Fletcher','Tradeskill','Unknown',25,25,'The Far Seas Trading Company has had an unusual and urgent order: a customer has requested custom arrows, to be manufactured using specific ingredients she has provided. Cordelia has asked me if I will attempt the work, and says she will meet me up at the Highland Outpost.',0,'I assisted Cordelia by creating arrows for their customer, according to her specific directions and using the ingredients she provided.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4714,'Smith-on-the-Spot','Tradeskill','Unknown',25,25,'Bartleby has had news that a shipment of equipment destined for Fort Irontoe has somehow been lost on the way. Although he has sent word for the supply headquarters to send more, there are a few urgent requirements that can\'t wait that long. He has asked me to help him forge equipment to replace what was lost.',0,'I assisted Bartleby by helping him to replace the most urgent items from the Far Seas supply shipment that was lost on the way to Fort Irontoe.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4715,'The Bear Essentials','Tradeskill','Unknown',25,25,'Cordelia has obtained a large number of bear teeth and claws from the local trapper. She has suggested that I use them to craft charms that might be more useful, not to mention less smelly.',0,'I helped Cordelia to make good use of the bear teeth and claws obtained from the local trapper, by crafting them into bear charms for her to use or trade.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4716,'Turning Turtle','Tradeskill','Unknown',25,25,'Cordelia has observed the dwarves making armor from local beetle shells, but thinks that turtle shells might make a more sturdy defense. She has some notes on turtle shell shield recipes she\'s been working on, and has asked me to test them for her.',0,'I assisted Cordelia by testing out her designs for turtle shell shields. She was pleased with the results, and said I was welcome to keep a copy of her recipe for my own use also.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4717,'Good Ore Bad?','Tradeskill','Unknown',25,25,'Bartleby thanked me for my assistance, and asked me to deliver some of the ore samples I collected to Karalyn Cinderton, currently working in the Steamfont Mountains. She is apparently an expert in assaying ore quality and he would like her second opinion on the samples.',0,'On behalf of Bartleby, I delivered the ore samples from the Mortartoe Mines to Karalyn Cinderton in the Steamfont Mountains. She will do further tests to confirm the quality of the ore if it is as good as expected.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4718,'Dirt Digging','Tradeskill','Unknown',30,30,'It seems a group of explorers have started a dig site in Butcherblock Mountains. They are searching for fossils of a creature which apparently lived in the mountains in ages past. Ellerith Groundspark has asked that I collect some of the fossils from around the area and return them to him for study.',0,'I was able to collect several fossils for Ellerith and his group. Hopefully this will help them in their studies.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4719,'Further Research','Tradeskill','Unknown',30,30,'Ellerith has asked that I speak with Gallie Shimmercloud, an associate of Rell Ver\'nief. She is helping him to research a magical process for extracting the essence of a creature from a fossilized egg. Apparently, they need some help in their research, which I might be able to help to provide.',0,'I was able to help Gallie and Rell research part of the ritual necessary to extract the saliraptors from the fossilized eggs.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4720,'Over Their Heads','Tradeskill','Unknown',30,30,'Ellerith has asked that I make a set of tents for the excavators, since they are currently working and sleeping out in the sun. He has given me a recipe with instructions to make a strong tent, which should hopefully provide sturdy cover for the working team.',0,'I was able to make the tents, and the excavators should be much better protected. Moreover, it seems that the assistance I lent to Gallie and Rell impressed them so much, that they offered me a reward for my help - a saliraptor they successfully extracted, which I can now use as a mount!','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4721,'Tools For Their Trade','Tradeskill','Unknown',30,30,'Ellerith has asked that I go and purchase some new tools for the excavators, since theirs are getting dull. I need to check the merchant down by the docks to see if they received a shipment of tools lately, and pick up five sets for the team.',0,'I was able to buy the necessary tools and return them to Ellerith and his team.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4722,'Beaks Away!','Tradeskill','Unknown',35,35,'Jamie instructed me to place the reinforced target dummy in the testing range, and try using their Troll Snot Flinger, Gnarmy!, and Tinkered Turkey Launcher weapon prototypes on it to test its durability.',0,'The reinforced target dummy successfully withstood testing the Troll Snot Flinger, the Gnarmy! and the Tinkered Turkey Launcher prototypes. The researchers were very pleased with my work and thanked me sincerely.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4723,'Building A Better Dummy, Part 1','Tradeskill','Unknown',35,35,'Adam Cogbuster and his compatriot Jamie are enthusiastic testers of the latest in tinkered weapons research. Unfortunately, they\'ve been having serious problems building test target dummies that actually stand up to the wear and tear of their testing procedures. Adam asked me to try and build them a more durable target dummy for their experiments.',0,'I created a sturdy target dummy for the researchers to use in their weapons testing.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4724,'Building A Better Dummy, Part 2','Tradeskill','Unknown',35,35,'Adam has asked me to try and build a more durable target dummy than my first attempt.',0,'I created a durable target dummy for the researchers to use in their weapons testing.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4725,'Building A Better Dummy, Part 3','Tradeskill','Unknown',35,35,'Adam has asked me to try reinforcing the target dummy to increase its chance of survival.',0,'I created a reinforced target dummy for the researchers to use in their weapons testing.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4726,'Essaying Assaying','Tradeskill','Unknown',35,35,'I have gathered all the materials Karalyn needed for the ore quality assay, and she has given me instructions on how to perform the tests myself.',0,'I used Karalyn Cinderton\'s instructions and performed an ore quality assay on the ore samples I brought from Bartleby in the Butcherblock Mountains. The results were excellent, and Karalyn has written to Bartleby to inform him that the ore is of the highest quality and he should attempt to trade for as much of it as he can.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4727,'Material Support','Tradeskill','Unknown',35,35,'Karalyn Cinderton needs some assistance in gathering the supplies she needs to complete the ore quality assay for Bartleby. I have offered to help if I can. She needs me to start by creating a device she\'s designed and using it to stun a clockwork and remove its battery so we can use the components for the assay.',0,'I crafted a clockwork zapper device and used it to disable a clockwork so I could remove its battery. The battery acid and copper coils will be needed to perform Karalyn Cinderton\'s ore quality assay.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4728,'Salt Of The Earth','Tradeskill','Unknown',35,35,'Karalyn Cinderton needs some salt for the ore assay, and has told me I can obtain some from the pure salt deposits that can form around the geysers and hotsprings in Steamfont.',0,'I gathered salt crystals from the pure deposits that form around the hotsprings and geysers in Steamfont, and returned them to Karalyn for use in her ore assay procedure.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4729,'\'Snot A Problem','Tradeskill','Unknown',35,35,'Jamie instructed me to place the target dummy in the testing range, and try using their Troll Snot Flinger weapon prototype on it to test its durability.',0,'Unfortunately, the sturdy target dummy disintegrated under the assault of the Troll Snot Flinger prototype.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4730,'You\'re In The Gnarmy Now','Tradeskill','Unknown',35,35,'Jamie instructed me to place the target dummy in the testing range, and try using their Troll Snot Flinger and Gnarmy! weapon prototypes on it to test its durability.',0,'Unfortunately, the durable target dummy combusted when tested with the Gnarmy! prototype.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4731,'Crafty Sootfoots: Another Man\'s Treasure','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'I have been asked to assist the Far Seas Trading Company in learning more about the Sootfoot goblins.',0,'I investigated the Sootfoot goblins and reported my findings for the Far Seas Trading Company.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4732,'Crafty Sootfoots: Corporate Espionage','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'I have been asked to assist the Far Seas Trading Company in learning more about the Sootfoot goblins.',0,'I investigated the Sootfoot goblins and reported my findings for the Far Seas Trading Company.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4733,'Crafty Sootfoots: Scouting About','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'I have been asked to assist the Far Seas Trading Company in learning more about the Sootfoot goblins.',0,'I investigated the Sootfoot goblins and reported my findings for the Far Seas Trading Company.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4734,'Sootfoot Service: Bellowing for Help','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'Smakametta has asked me to help repair the bellows for his forge, which are not pumping air properly.',0,'I managed to repair the bellows for Smakametta.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4735,'Sootfoot Service: Hot Rocks','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'Smakametta has promised to give me a copy of his recipes and one of the secret Sootfoot armor molds if I bring him some magma to make it with.',0,'I brought Smakametta the magma and he gave me his recipes, and also one of the secret Sootfoot armor molds.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4736,'Sootfoot Service: Ore Spillage','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'Smakametta now requires assistance in tidying up his ore bin and refilling its contents.',0,'I brought Smakametta the ore that he needed.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4737,'Sootfoot Service: Repairing the Repairs','Tradeskill','Unknown',45,45,'Smakametta says the chimney over his forge hasn\'t worked well since the Sootfoot carpenters offered to repair it. I will use the schematics he has and see if I can do a better job.',0,'I repaired the chimney for Smakametta and he was very grateful.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4738,'Soo