Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4815,'Tracking the Void Influence','Tradeskill','Unknown',85,85,'The Quel\'ule scholar Azira has requested assistance in applying a recording tag to a void creature to gather information for study.',0,'I assisted the researchers of Quel\'ule with their daily tasks.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4816,'Badger of Success','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'The badger pelts are now cured and ready to take back to the othmir. I offered to take the pelts back with me, and wished the gnolls good luck.',0,'I obtained some badger pelts from the snowfang gnolls and brought them back to the othmir Mira. I also helped to arrange an ongoing trade agreement between the othmir and gnolls which should be mutually beneficial to both.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4817,'Herbal Cure','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'I offered to show the gnoll Ruffin how to cure the snow badger pelts, using an astringent herbal solution.',0,'I showed Ruffin what herbs to gather, and how to mix up a solution to cure the snow badger pelts.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4818,'It\'s A Long Way Down','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'The gnolls are having difficulties obtaining enough fish due to the high cliffs to the west, and the dangerous creatures to the east. Their fishing rods are not long enough to fish from the higher cliffs, so they are unable to catch enough. I offered to see if I can obtain some extra-long fishing rods to help.',0,'I obtained some extra-long fishing rods for the gnolls to fish off the high cliffs surrounding their current camp.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4819,'Meet the Locals','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Matthew from the Far Seas Trading Company has asked me to speak to the othmir and learn more about what crafts and other items they might have for trade.',0,'I spoke to Mira the othmir about possible items for trade, and found out that the othmir value shells highly.Â ','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4820,'Pelt Parlay','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Mira asked me to cook some crab meat and take it to the nearby gnolls, to see if they would be willing to trade food for badger pelts.',0,'I cooked some crab meat and found a gnoll to speak to about the possibility of trade.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4821,'Shell Game','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Mira was interested by the recipe that Matthew offered to trade them, and in the meantime she asked me to gather some shells from the nearby ice floe where they wash up. She hoped the Far Seas Trading Company might find the shells valuable for trade.',0,'Mira hoped the Far Seas Trading Company might find shells valuable for trade, as the othmir prize them highly. However, Matthew seemed less than enthused with the shells, and asked me to investigate further possibilities.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4822,'Snappy Dressing','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Now that I have obtained all the components required, Mira has agreed to show me the othmir\'s recipe for shell armor.',0,'I learned how to make the othmir\'s shell armor.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4823,'Snappy Trapping','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Mira suggested that I check the traps I placed to see if anything has been caught yet. She will need crab sinews, crab shells, and snow cougar pelts to make the armor she mentioned.',0,'The improved model of traps that I made seemed to be very efficient and caught some Iceclad crabs almost immediately. Mira will use the crab sinews and shells to show me their armor recipe, and she asked me to cook the crab meat and take it to the snowfang gnolls in hopes they might trade for snow cougar pelts.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4824,'Snowfang Skinning','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'I offered to show the gnolls how to make a skinning knife, so that they can skin the snow badgers and use the pelts for trade.',0,'I found instructions for making skinning knives, and returned to the snowfang camp to show the gnoll how to make one.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4825,'Snowfang Starvation','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'I saw some edible roots of some sort growing in the area, and the gnolls say they can eat them, but they only grow for a short season and then are gone. I offered to teach the gnolls how to preserve the vegetables in jars so they can store them to eat all year.',0,'I taught the gnolls how to preserve vegetables for long-term storage so they can have the roots to eat all year around.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4826,'Snowy Business','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Matthew is interested in what kind of armor the othmir can make from shells and the limited materials in the area. He has asked me to investigate further.',0,'Matthew was interested in the othmir\'s shell armor and sent me to learn more from Mira.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4827,'Trap Trip','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Mira says more shells and shellfish are needed to craft the othmir special armor. She suggested I take this opportunity to test the new trap design the Far Seas Trading Company has offered to trade them.',0,'I tested out the Far Seas Trading Company trap recipe by making and placing a number of the traps.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4828,'A Case of Mistaken Monstrosity','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Misa asked me to check and see if the trap has caught any monsters yet. It seems unlikely, but I agreed to check.',0,'I discovered the &quot;monster&quot; trap had caught an innocent froglok traveler, a healer who has come to Velious to study the area. While trying to disarm the trap I placed for Misa, she accidentally got trapped inside. I released her with apologies and returned to tell Misa that her &quot;monster&quot; is not a monster at all.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4829,'A Heartfelt Thank You','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Arjon seems overcome with appreciation for the help and healing that Finnegan provided. Since he is still supposed to be resting and recovering, he asked me if I would help him express his gratitude and admiration by delivering a bunch of flowers and a thank you letter to her.',0,'I picked some pretty local flowers and delivered them with Arjon\'s letter to Finnegan.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4830,'Dinner For Two','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'The preparations for dinner are complete, and Arjon just has to finish the cooking. He has asked me to deliver his dinner invitation to Finnegan while he prepares the meal.',0,'I delivered Arjon\'s dinner invitation to Finnegan, who accepted with pleasure and agreed to meet Arjon at the dock at the appropriate time. I wished them both luck.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4831,'Errand of Mercy','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Misa has received news that her father was injured while on patrol. His patrol-mate has gone to try and find the local healer, but Misa wondered if the froglok healer we accidentally trapped earlier might agree to help him. I offered to go and ask, if I can find her again.',0,'I found the froglok healer Finnegan, and explained Misa\'s injured father needed help. She agreed to accompany me and see if she could help him.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4832,'Escort Duty','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Misa asked me to check back on her father, and help escort him back to their home.',0,'I returned to Misa\'s father Arjon, and as Finnegan had healed the worst of his injuries, I escorted him safely home to Misa.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4833,'Monster, Monster!','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Misa saw me carrying the shellfish traps around for Mira, and asked me to make her one for trapping monsters. She is convinced she saw monster tracks in the snow near the fishing area. She told me to go and see for myself, since I seemed dubious.',0,'I inspected the area where Misa said she saw monster tracks. I had to admit I did see some marks that looked like the flipper track Misa described, although I did not see any monsters.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4834,'Mood Music','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Arjon asked for my assistance in making a traditional othmir drum, so that Finnegan can enjoy the traditional music and culture of the othmir.',0,'Finnegan received the traditional othmir drum with thanks, and looked forward to hearing it played.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4835,'Necessary Preparations','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Misa was glad to hear her father has a healer helping and should be home again soon. She is now in a panic to get everything ready and comfortable for his convalescence, and begged me to make a comfortable cushion for his bed.',0,'I obtained a cushion recipe from the Far Seas trader, and stitched up a comfortable cushion for Misa\'s father.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4836,'On the Defensive','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Misa is worried about protecting herself and her father from the monsters. She asked me to take some of her father\'s damaged old weapons and use them to make a sturdy weapon for her to defend her family with.',0,'I used the old weapons discarded by Misa\'s father to make her a sturdy club.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4837,'Setting the Scene','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Arjon asked if I could help him by constructing a small portable table, and delivering it to the dock where he plans to have dinner and watch the sunset with Finnegan. He gave me a recipe, and I agreed to assist.',0,'I helped Arjon get ready for dinner with Finnegan by constructing a small portable table and placing it at the dock, where he plans to have dinner and watch the sunset with Finnegan.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4838,'Special Ingredients','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Arjon is planning to cook a fine dinner for Finnegan, and has asked me to gather some of the local edible shellfish for him, since he is not yet able to do so himself. I agreed to assist.',0,'I assisted Arjon in his dinner preparations by diving for the tasty abalone shellfish that cling to the nearby ice shelf. Since Arjon is not yet recovered enough to go diving himself, he was very grateful for the help.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4839,'Trap Happy','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Misa begged me to make a trap for her to prove there is a monster. I agreed to do so, if only to calm her down.',0,'I crafted a large trap and placed it where the supposed &quot;monster&quot; tracks were found.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4840,'Aid to the East','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Mira has heard the othmir settlement of Nipik\'s Haven could use some assistance, but the journey is long and dangerous for othmir. She has asked me to fly there instead and see if I can offer any help.',0,'I traveled to Nipik\'s Haven in the Eastern Wastes and made contact with the othmir called Livi.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4841,'Letter to Thurgadin','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Finnegan asked me to return a borrowed map to the gnomish pirates in Thurgadin, if I was heading in that direction.Â ',0,'I returned the map that the gnomish pirates had lent to Finnegan to assist in her attempts to find evidence of Brell\'s supposed manifestation in the area many centuries ago.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4842,'Better Living Through Tinkering','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Fenwick has asked for my assistance once more. He would like me to tinker up a new distillery for gnomish pirate spirits, as their old one was recently destroyed in what he called an &quot;unfortunate spontaneous combustion incident&quot;.',0,'I followed Fenwick\'s directions and tinkered up a new distillery for making the special gnomish pirate spirits.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4843,'Clockwork Dockwork','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Pirate Fenwick said my assistance would be most helpful around the dock if I can spare the time to repair some broken widgets.',0,'I helped the gnomish pirates repair some of the broken widgets on the dock.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4844,'Clockwork Spybots','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Pirate Fenwick has asked for my skilled assistance in tinkering up a spybot to monitor the activities of the Order of Rime.',0,'I assisted the gnomish pirates of Thurgadin by tinkering up a mechanical spybot that will provide surveillance of the activities of the Order of Rime.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4845,'High Spirits','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Fenwick has asked me to test the new distillery by brewing up a batch of the gnomish pirates\' special pirate spirits. I will need to gather the ingredients first, as they need to be freshly obtained.',0,'I gathered the ingredients and made a batch of the special gnomish pirate spirits. Fenwick was pleased with the results, which he said would put a sea beasty to sleep.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4846,'Oomba\'s Boomba','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Pirate Oomba continues to invent new gadgets, and has asked me to build the prototype for a mechanical self-guided explosive, which he calls the &quot;Boomba&quot;.',0,'I followed the instructions from the large gnomish pirate Oomba, and created a prototype of a mechanical self-guided clockwork for him. He calls it the &quot;Boomba&quot;. This clockwork was able to travel towards the Order of Rime fortifications and then self-destruct explosively. Since Oomba seems to be extremely good at creating unstable, explosive clockworks, the Boomba seems to be an excellent use of his talents!','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4847,'Oomba\'s Loomba','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'The rather large gnomish pirate Oomba seems full of invention ideas, and needs someone to build the prototypes for him while he continues brainstorming new inventions. He has asked me to create an automated tailoring clockwork, which he plans to call the &quot;Loomba&quot;.Â ',0,'I followed the instructions from the rather large gnomish pirate Oomba, and created a prototype of a mechanical tailoring clockwork for him. He called it the &quot;Loomba&quot;. Unfortunately, the clockwork caught fire and self destructed before it was able to sew anything.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4848,'Oomba\'s Zoomba','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Pirate Oomba continues to plan his new inventions, and would now like me to build the prototype for a mechanical cleaner, which he plans to call the &quot;Zoomba&quot;.',0,'I followed the instructions from the rather large gnomish pirate Oomba, and created a prototype of a mechanical cleaner for him. He called it the &quot;Zoomba&quot;. Unfortunately, the prototype self-combusted before it could clean anything.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4849,'Tinkered Technology','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Pirate Fenwick has asked for my assistance with a number of tasks that require a skilled tinkerer. The first of these is to reassure Captain Nalot\'s worries about a &quot;beasty&quot; attacking, by tinkering up an advanced warning system.',0,'I tinkered up an Advanced Beasty Warning System and delivered it to Captain Nalot.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4850,'Toasting the Creator','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Fenwick deemed my gnomish pirate spirits to be of fine quality, and so has requested that I leave a small bottle of it as an offering at the temple of Brell.',0,'Although the gnomes are less demonstrative about it than dwarves, they appreciate their creator, Brell, and believe that he enjoys a good strong offering of gnomish spirits to offset all the dwarven ale. At Fenwick\'s request, I left a small bottle of the spirits at Brell\'s altar.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4851,'Blessings for the Grandson','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Eirik needs to hurry back to his injured grandson with the healing stew, but has asked me to take a bowl of the stew and leave it as an offering at Brell\'s temple on behalf of his grandson.',0,'Eirik explained that his grandson has been badly injured fighting the Rime, so Eirik needs to deliver the healing stew to help him recover. He headed off to take most of the stew to his grandson, but he left a bowl with me and asked me to leave it as an offering at the temple of Brell, on behalf of his grandson. I agreed to do him this favor.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4852,'Healing Leaves','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'The old coldain Eirik seemed to need assistance. He wanted to make his famous stew, but was unable to gather the ingredients needed. I offered to go into the mountains and gather the leaves he needs.',0,'Eirik is too old to climb the icy cliffs to gather the special ingredient he needs to flavor his traditional healing stew. I offered to gather the plant leaves for him, and returned with the amount he needed.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4853,'Healing Stew Brew','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Eirik has asked me to help him make his traditional coldain healing stew.',0,'I cooked up a batch of Eirik\'s traditional healing stew, which he claims will almost bring the dead back to life and make the living forget all their ills.Â ','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4854,'News From Home','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'I met a coldain called Alfrig in the temple. He had heard news that the old Dain\'s ring had been found, and asked me to let his mother Tora know if I was passing by the region of the old Ring War.',0,'I found Tora at the site of the old ring war and gave her the news from her son Alfrig.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4855,'Cannons Away','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Aggi has asked me to use the recipe from the gnomish pirates to craft a heavy gnomish cannon. She would like me to place this among the furthest fortifications in Storm Gorge to help defend against the attack of the Rime.',0,'I crafted a heavy gnomish cannon for Aggi, and left it with the advance defenders to help defend Thurgadin against the Rime.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4856,'Far Seas Negotiations','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Aggi planned to begin her hawk training efforts by ordering an experienced trained hawk from the Far Seas Trading Company. She has just received word that Matthew, the company\'s representative in Velious, has received her shipment. She asked me if I would mind going to collect the hawk from him.',0,'I agreed to assist Aggi in starting her hawk training program by collecting the trained hawk that she had ordered. The trader Matthew had received the trained hawk that Aggi ordered from the Far Seas Trading Company, and I brought it safely back to Aggi.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4857,'Gilded Cages','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Aggi is planning to obtain some trained hawks to fly surveillance over the Order of Rime\'s locations. She has asked me to craft some comfortable cages to keep them in between missions.',0,'I crafted some comfortable cages that Aggi\'s hawks will be able to rest in between surveillance missions.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4858,'Gnomish Gnegotiations','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Aggi is assisting with the defense of Thurgadin against the Order of Rime. She asked if I could speak to the gnomish pirates in the dock area, and see if they would be willing to give her a recipe for their gnomish cannons.',0,'I obtained a recipe for the gnomish cannons, and brought it back to Aggi, who is assisting with the defense of Thurgadin against the Order of Rime.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4859,'Scouring the Peaks','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Now Aggi has a trained hawk and some spare cages, she needs to obtain more hawks. She would like to start training some of the local hawks, but this requires finding some nests so they can be trained from very young. She has asked me to head up into the mountain peaks to see if I can find any hawk nests.',0,'I learned that this is not the right season for the mountain hawks to breed; Aggi is going to have to wait a few more months before she can obtain any young eyas.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4860,'Wings Away','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Aggi asked me to take the hawk out for a test flight. She wants me to release it near the furthest barricades in Storm Gorge, and confirm it flies over the Rime fortifications as trained.',0,'I released the trained hawk in Storm Gorge, and it flew over the Rime barricades as expected. By the time I returned to Aggi to report the successful test flight, the hawk had already returned to her.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4861,'Anti-Rime Ammunition','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'The supply requests that have reached Mikk Eishammer today state that the lightweight gnomish cannons they are testing have been a great success in the defense of Storm Gorge, but they tend to occasionally self-combust, and as a result the defenders are starting to run short of cannons. He has asked me if I will assist them in making more.',0,'Since the lightweight gnomish cannons already supplied to the troops apparently occasionally suffer a bad case of self-combustion, supplies were running low. Fortunately I was able to assist Mikk Eishammer in crafting more to replace those that were destroyed.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4862,'Defending the Defenders','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'The brave troops defending Thurgadin from the forces of the Rime are always in need of additional armor supplies. Mikk Eishammer has asked me to help fill some urgent orders which arrived today.',0,'I helped Mikk Eishammer to fill the urgent orders for more armor for the coldain troops.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4863,'Dwarven Fuel','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Mikk Eishammer told me that today is a day off for many of the army cooks of Thurgadin, so he is recruiting extra help to get tonight\'s meal ready for the troops. He seems to be hoping I will volunteer.',0,'I stepped forward to assist Mikk Eishammer in making enough hearty stew to feed the brave defenders of Thurgadin.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4864,'Explosive Powder','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Mikk Eishammer has received urgent reports that the explosive powder used to fuel the gnomish cannons is running out. He is asking for volunteers to assist in crafting more to keep Thurgadin\'s defenses strong.',0,'I crafted more of the explosive gnomish cannon powder to keep the gnomish cannons firing and the defenders of Thurgadin safe.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4865,'Icy Artifacts','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Today Mikk Eishammer is recruiting additional helpers to assist the researchers studying the old Ring War battle site. They need someone to travel to the site and search for more relics.',0,'I assisted the coldain researchers by bringing them more relics to study from the old Ring War battle site.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4866,'Stoking the Flames','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Mikk Eishammer has received reports that the signal fires that blaze around Thurgadin are running low on fuel. He is offering a few coin and his good favor to anyone who has time to help gather more driftwood to fuel the fires.',0,'I helped Mikk Eishammer by gathering driftwood to fuel the signal fires around Thurgadin.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4867,'Supplies for Thurgadin','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Mikk Eishammer has received a request from the Thurgadin chefs for more brontotherium meat for their stews. He has asked me to go out and gather more if I have the time.',0,'I gathered a sufficient amount of brontotherium meat to keep the cooks of Thurgadin busy feeding the troops.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4868,'A Keener Sheen','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'The coat of my young gryphon pet is looking a bit rough, and has lost some luster. A healthy homemade conditioner should return the fur to a healthy sheen.',0,'I cleaned my young gryphon\'s coat. If I continue to care for her she will grow closer to me and be sure to listen to my commands.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4869,'Dream Weaving','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'When I returned to Capru with the news that the snowfang shamans do indeed have a way of catching dreams, he asked me if I would obtain one for him. I offered to make him one.',0,'I followed the directions that Ruffin gave me, and made a dream catcher for Capru to try. He was eager to test it out and did not seem to want to talk to me further right then, but he told me to return later if I wished more work. When I returned, he explained that his previous tasks have been testing my reliability, patience, and compassion for animals. It seems that I passed these tests, as he has entrusted me with the care of a young gryphon, explaining that as his village is currently under threat from the Order of Rime, some of them feel it would be safer for some of the young gryphons to be cared for by trusted outsiders like myself.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4870,'Fishy Treats for Hungry Beaks','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'My young gryphon friend looks hungry. I should find some Iceclad cutlassfish to feed her!',0,'I got some Iceclad cutlassfish meat for my gryphon. If I continue to care for her she will grow strong enough to fly while carrying my weight.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4871,'Growing Pains','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'I noticed my young gryphon seems to have a small scratch on her forearm! I\'d better bandage it up carefully so it will keep clean and heal well.',0,'I noticed my young gryphon had a small scratch on her forearm! I made some bandages and wrapped the scratch up well to keep clean and dry. If I continue to care for my young gryphon, she will grow disciplined enough to fly with me on her back.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4872,'Hungry Hungry Spiders','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Capru is worried about the health of the young spiderlings he is trying to rear. Apparently they are unwell, and he is not able to catch enough insects in the cold mountain air to feed them properly. Noting that he has observed I love animals, he asked me to make a suitable trap and retrieve a number of large, juicy insects from some more fertile jungle climate that might provide enough nourishment for the spiderlings.',0,'I created an insect trap and traveled to the Feerrott to obtain some of the juicy damselflies that swarm that region. Apparently these will be perfect nourishment to help Capru\'s crystalline spiderlings recover.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4873,'Meaty Meals for a Growing Gryphon','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'My young gryphon pet looks hungry. I should find some brontotherium meat to feed her!',0,'I got some fresh killed meat for my young gryphon. If I continue to care for her she will grow strong enough to fly while carrying my weight.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4874,'Mend These Broken Wings','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'One of Capru\'s regular tasks is to mix up healing salves so the village has enough on hand in case a gryphon is injured. Apparently he is running low currently, and, knowing my fondness for animals, he has asked me if I would help by gathering the herbs he will need to make the salves.',0,'Believing in my fondness for animals, Capru asked me to assist him by gathering some medicinal herbs from the area so that he can restock the village\'s supply of healing salve that they keep on hand for the gryphons.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4875,'Milly\'s Meals','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Because I pet his crystalline spiderlings, Capru got the impression I am fond of animals. He\'s therefore asked me if I would like to feed his pet Milly by bringing her an iceclad cutlassfish.',0,'I obtained an iceclad cutlassfish to bring to Capru\'s pet Milly. Apparently the fish oil makes her carapace plates gleam even more brightly. Capru assures me she is an intelligent and affectionate creature who greatly appreciates my gesture...','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4876,'Playing Fetch','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'My young gryphon friend could use some exercise. A game of fetch with a bone should be good exercise!',0,'I played fetch with my young gryphon friend. I will continue to care for my gryphon and she will be sure to listen to my commands.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4877,'Snug as a Bug','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Capru explained his people\'s close relationship with the snow gryphons of Velious, and how they often assist in caring for the eggs and young while the parents are unwell or absent, as well as assisting injured gryphons as needed. Apparently the current clutch of eggs is in need of assistance as its parents are unable to care for it, and Capru would like my assistance in weaving some warm, soft padding to keep the eggs and hatchlings safe and cosy.',0,'Capru explained his people\'s close relationship with the snow gryphons of Velious, and how they often assist in caring for the eggs and young gryphons while the parents are unwell or absent, as well as assisting injured griffins as needed. Apparently the current clutch of eggs was in need of assistance as its parents are unable to care for it, so I assisted by weaving some of the crystalline spiderling silk into warm, cosy padding to protect the eggs and young gryphons.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4878,'To Capture a Dream','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Capru has heard rumors that the snowfang gnoll shamans have a way to capture dreams and visions. He would like me to learn more about this if it is true.',0,'Capru was interested in learning more about the methods of the snowfang shamans for catching dreams and visions. I offered to speak to my acquaintance Ruffin, and learned from him how to make the dream catchers that the snowfang shamans make.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4879,'Hunting for History','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Tora has reluctantly admitted that she could use the help of a skilled artisan, even one that is not a coldain, so she has instructed me to make myself an ice pick and carefully chisel into the ice of the battlefield in search of relics.',0,'Tora reluctantly admitted that she could use the help of a skilled artisan, so she instructed me to make myself an ice pick and use it to search the battlefield for relics of the war. It appears I was extraordinarily lucky with my first find, which was the handle of an axe that might have belonged to her ancestor General Bragmur himself.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4880,'Inside the Vision','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Tora instructed me to focus my thoughts on her ancestor by inhaling the perfumed smoke from the herbs, and touching the axe that belonged to him. If her ritual is successful, we may be able to contact his spirit to try and learn some way to free the ghosts from their trapped state.',0,'Tora\'s ritual worked to some extent: I was able to make contact with her ancestor General Bragmur, but the great guilt she feels prevented her from seeing or hearing him. I discovered the reason for her guilt, and that of all the coldain: the ring war warriors were not killed at the hands of the giants, but by their own kindred, who used the waterfall to flood the entire battlefield and end the war. Because of this, the spirits of the Ring War warriors are trapped in their current state, unable to leave this realm for the Halls of the Creator, instead reliving the final battle over and over. Unfortunately, Bragmur did not know of any force less powerful than Brell\'s own blessing that could free them from this endless cycle.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4881,'Ritual Gathering','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'In order to perform the ritual to contact the spirit of her ancestor, Tora needs to burn some aromatic herbs. She has asked me to obtain the herbs while she prepares for the ritual. She noted the location of the herbs in my journal.',0,'I obtained the herbs Tora needed for the ritual to contact her ancestor while Tora prepared for the ritual.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4882,'The Cutting Edge','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Tora was excited by the axe handle I found, and asked me to search further to see if I could locate the blade of the axe that fits the handle.',0,'I was able to locate the missing axe blade that fit the axe handle I found earlier. Tora hopes that the complete axe may help her make contact with the spirit of her ancestor General Bragmur.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4883,'Salivating for Sabotage','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Livi instructed me to treat the axes I stole earlier with a solution of the ancient wurms\' saliva, and then return to the forest and replace the deforesters\' spare axes with the ones I had weakened with the saliva treatment.',0,'I weakened the axes I took earlier by treating them with a wurm saliva solution, then returned to the forest and replaced the deforesters\' spare axes with the weakened ones.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4884,'Sampling the Damage','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Livi has asked for my assistance in slowing the deforestation. She instructed me to gather the axes that the Duhjalm deforesters leave lying around.',0,'I gathered some of the axes that were left unattended by the Duhjalm deforesters.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4885,'Surveying the Land','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Livi described the giants\' destruction of the nearby forests, and asked me to help determine the location of the deforesters close to the othmir.',0,'I visited the Flamespout Fields, formerly a mighty forest, and cataloged the location of a Duhjalm deforester very near to the othmir.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4886,'Thunder in the Hills','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Livi described how the othmir had heard a &quot;thunder in the hills&quot; and felt a great shaking of the ground some time back, but that they have been unable to determine the cause due to all the giant activity in the area. She asked me to use a flying mount and investigate more closely for them whether it is something that might concern the othmir.',0,'The othmir reported a loud noise in the mountains and a shaking of the ground had preceded the increase of activity by the giants. They had been unable to safely learn more, but asked me to investigate further and let them know if it was anything of concern. I discovered that an imposing structure has appeared on the mountains near Kael Drakkel, made of a strange substance I had never before seen in Norrath. Inside I observed a statue that indicated some sort of tie to the god of war, Rallos Zek.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4887,'A Holy Adventure','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'I need to find a master cleric and an expert gnomish experimenter. The Temple of Brell should have a few priests, and Thunderstomp probably knows of a gnomish experimenter.',0,'I have spoken to a cleric, and he has agreed to provide me with his blessing. Now, I must seek out Thunderstomp\'s uncle in Steamfont and convince him to craft a device capable of breaking the bonds.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4888,'Accuracy is Everything','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'I need to get this binding sample analyzed. With it properly evaluated, we can begin to formulate a plan to break the bindings on the Thudomatonians.',0,'I have received a Canister of Dispel Magic from Arthex. He suggested that I contact a tinkerer and a master cleric for further assistance. This should be interesting.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4889,'Assaulting the Chains','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'I need to return to Brontis and break him free!',0,'I have broken the Thudomatonians out of their bindings, which should disrupt the flow of arms to the armies of war! As a token of their thanks, Brontis has agreed to share the ancient recipes of the Thudomatonians with me.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4890,'Bindings of Brontis','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'The Thudomatonian Constructs are being forced to craft the tools of war against their will. I must find a way to free them!',0,'I have talked to an...&quot;expert&quot; about the bindings on Brontis and the Thudomatonians. I should follow the lead that the gnomish bard has given me.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4891,'Blessing the Bit','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'I need to craft the drill, and then get it blessed by Mergus.',0,'I have crafted the drill and it has been blessed by Mergus. I should now use it to free the Thudomatonians!','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4892,'Doing the Dirty Work','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'I need to craft a massive heatsink for Lumzig.',0,'I have created a massive heatsink for Lumzig. In return, he has granted me the schematic and resources required to craft the drill I need.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4893,'Gnome Hunt','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'I need to find Thunderstomp\'s uncle Lumzig in Steamfont.',0,'I have found Lumzig. However, he wants me to create a heatsink for him before he will assist me.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4894,'Thudomatonian Monotony','Tradeskill','Unknown',90,90,'Frizella asked me to craft a Pocket-Sized Dimensional Trap. After crafting this, I need to fill it with a sample of Brontis\' bindings.',0,'I used the trap to get a sample of Brontis\' bindings. I need to bring this sample back to Frizella.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4895,'A Mystery Satyr','Tradeskill','Unknown',91,91,'I need to find the Satyr that Porto was talking about. He gave me a general location to search.',0,'I have found the satyr named Phaerus Thunderhorn. I should find out what he wants.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4896,'Preserving the Flank','Tradeskill','Unknown',91,91,'Porto Bunglefoot, the Combine\'s solitary chef, needs me to help him properly treat some mammoth meat.',0,'I returned the treated mammoth meat to Porto.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4897,'Replacement Supplies','Tradeskill','Unknown',91,91,'Porto wants me to create new supplies for the camp. I will need materials harvested from the forest.',0,'I have given the replacement supplies to Porto.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4898,'A Timeless','Tradeskill','Unknown',0,0,'',0,'','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4899,'A Helping Hand','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'I ran into Quentin again, and it seems that Field Marshal Vishra has something he needs from me. I should report to him, at Scarstone, immediately.',0,'Vishra has entrusted me with an artifact handed down through his family line, the Hands of the Maker. These gloves are unlike anything I\'ve ever seen, I can\'t even fathom how they were made. I\'ve promised Vishra that I\'ll use them well, and when I or my descendants find we have no use for them, to return them to the Bayle line.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4900,'A Lethal Contingency','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'As her final request, Plex has asked me to brew up seven doses of quick, lethal, painless poison. I have a feeling I know what they\'ll be used for, and given the difficulty in making a poison that fulfills all three requirements, Plex has asked that I focus on the painless aspect if I need to prioritize. I hope this is the right decision.',0,'The poison is complete, and in Plex\'s possession. I wish I could do more, I can only hope that I\'ve done enough.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4901,'A Roof Over Our Heads','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'I had an idea about how to keep those wyrms out of our camp if they make an aerial attack. We can make a device that will blast a massive force screen above our heads. It\'ll require a lot of energy, and Angor doesn\'t quite know how to approach that problem, so I\'ll be building the power source while he works on the projection technology.Â ',0,'With some effort, I\'ve built the Force Projector\'s power source. Now we just need to put it together.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4902,'Adding a Little Something','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Grant has given me a recipe for his Cobalt Chiori paste. It\'s simple, but the Chiori has enough flavor that I think it can hold up on its own. Should have about 6,000 servings of it by the time I\'m done.Â ',0,'I\'ve finished making the Cobalt Chiori paste for Grant\'s rations. It\'s a good idea, and I think our soldiers will appreciate it.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4903,'Applying Hope','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Having made Hope, the next step is to use it in the field and see if it\'s up to the task. I\'ve given some to Yeppa and his warriors, and I\'ll be using the rest. If we use it on enough of these bones, the enchantment should abate, and help to see this land return to its normal state.',0,'We\'ve applied Hope to a large number of bones, but it seems that the bones are not the source of the scourge. They seem to only broadcast it from somewhere else. Hope was effective, but only for a brief period before the bones were suffused with corruption again. I should hold onto it though, it will likely be key in whatever I need to do next.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4904,'Bone and Marrow','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'After using the Necromantic Detector, it seems that these large bone structures are likely the source of what\'s causing the undeath of this area. I\'m going to take a sample from these bones and see if I can\'t discover why they\'re spreading this scourge. Once I have that answer, hopefully I\'ll be able to find a way to counter it.',0,'I\'ve determined the kind of magic that is causing this, but it is extremely powerful. It\'s going to take something equally exotic to counter.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4905,'Communicating With Our Destiny','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'The next thing that Plex requires is a set of cloaks that can turn their wearers invisible. I need some exotic materials for that, which Plex and her crew are going to gather for me. In the meantime, Plex needs a set of communication devices. Whisperstones are common enough, and as much as I hate to do it, Fahris can probably provide me with some.',0,'It seems that Fahris has been demoted, and Grant has taken his place as camp Quartermaster! He was able to get me the whisperstones Plex needs without any difficulty at all. He\'s going to be a great replacement for Fahris.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4906,'Corrupted Spring Investigation','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'There\'s something fishy going on in the main New Combine camp. Each and every ballista has a badly corroded torsion spring installed. If someone was to try firing them, it wouldn\'t work, and worse, would likely catastrophically fail - bad news for the ballista operator. I\'m going to check these springs out and run some tests to see if I can\'t figure out the source of the corrosion.',0,'After seriously examining these springs, I can tell they\'ve been enchanted with some fairly strong corruption magic, almost certainly the work of a Defiler.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4907,'Countertrap!','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'We don\'t know who the saboteur is yet, but we will soon! I\'ve devised a compound that will react to corruption magic - combining that with a dye will make plain the identity of the saboteur. I\'ve written the instructions in my recipe book.',0,'I\'ve applied the compound to the ballistae, and now, we wait. Denstarin will have patrols scouring the camp for anyone marked with the dye, so it is only a matter of time...','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4908,'Crafting the Perfect Solution','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Now that we have the ice, we need to distill it down and create an alchemical solution that will protect the tents from the wyrms\' magical assault.Â ',0,'I\'ve distilled the essence down precisely and combined it with Angor\'s treatment. He was duly impressed.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4909,'Creating Hope','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'The blue flower I\'ve found is likely to be the key ingredient in my enchantment-breaking salve. It needs to be strong enough to overcome the incredibly powerful magic here, but if I\'m right, the flower should do the trick. I think I\'ll call the salve &quot;Hope,&quot; as that\'s what it represents to Yeppa and his people.Â ',0,'I\'ve finished making Hope, now it\'s time to see whether my skills are up to the task or not.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4910,'Creating the Amber Storm','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'I met a mysterious woman just outside the New Combine camp. Her name is Plex, and she has a list of equipment she and her team need for an upcoming mission. The Quartermaster, Fahris, is unsurprisingly unwilling to assist her, and so she\'s asked me to provide what he cannot. The first thing on my list is ten stone of amber storm fulminant, a powerful explosive.',0,'I\'ve created ten stone worth of amber storm fuliminant, and returned it to Plex.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4911,'Delivering the Delivery','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'I need to locate the delivery team responsible for the siege gearing supply. They may have been waylaid on the way here, and I need to find them, dead or alive.',0,'I\'ve found the remains of the delivery team. Though they have perished, I was able to recover the package they were responsible for.Â ','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4912,'Final Touches','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'This is the final stretch - if Angor has done his homework, then it should be a simple matter of putting his work and mine together.',0,'The Force Projector is complete! Should any wyrms decide to attack from the air, they\'ll get a nasty surprise!','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4913,'Finding Hope','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'After investigating the enchantment on these bones, I\'m in awe of the power of them. Something upsettingly terrible is infused within, and it will take something special and antithetical to the enchantment to break it. I\'m on the search for that now - if I can find a beast, a shrub, anything living that is resisting the scourge, then we might be able to use that to counter what\'s happening here.',0,'I\'ve found a blue flower growing from the corpse of one of the slain risen Othmir. I\'m hoping that this is the counter that I\'m looking for.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4914,'Fuel for the Fire','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'I need to gather some Cobalt Chiori to help the Acting Supplymaster, Grant. He\'s a nervous sort that doesn\'t believe in himself. He\'s got talent, just needs some confidence, and I aim to fix that.',0,'I\'ve given Grant the Cobalt Chiori that he needs. This should get those New Combine soldiers plenty amped up!','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4915,'Hope Reborn','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'While Hope ultimately failed, I believe that we may be barking up the wrong tree. There\'s got to be something else here that\'s recharging the scourge, powering it, so I\'m going to retool my Necromantic Detector and see if I can\'t find the true source. If I can, Hope should be effective in breaking the enchantment. If I somehow lose Hope, I\'ll probably need to go see if those flowers are still growing and make it again.',0,'The Necromantic Detector worked! It lead me down a series of caves, where I ultimately found a very disturbing... altar of sorts. At it\'s center was a huge dragon skull, which sent my detector off the charts. After applying Hope, the scourge seems to have abated, and I think I can call this a success. It will take a long, long time before the scourge dissipates, but at least Yeppa\'s brethren will be able to find some peace.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4916,'Icing the Competition','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Angor, an interesting fellow concerned about the vulnerability of the camp to a wyrm attack, has asked me to collect some enchanted ice that accumulates from the cold wind on the cliffs here. Once I have about a stone\'s worth, I should return it to him.Â ',0,'I\'ve returned to the camp with the enchanted ice. Let\'s see what we can do with it!','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4917,'Iron Rations for an Iron Army','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'We need to finish up the Iron Rations that Grant is making. He and his crew are still a little slow, and it\'s up to me to help them finish all this on time.',0,'I\'ve finished off the remaining rations - they look good and should be plenty nutritious.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4918,'Locating the Lost','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'The othmir that arrived with the supply caravan have run off somewhere. They need to be found, and if I can locate them, I should see about getting them back in touch with the main contingent.',0,'I\'ve found Yeppa and his companions, but they are overrun by undead othmir! They obviously need help, and I should see what I can do to get them out of the predicament they\'re in.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4919,'Multiplication Tables','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Buildmaster Angor is having trouble with the force multiplier component of the projection unit. I need to see if I can get it done.Â ',0,'The force multiplier has been fixed, the issue seemed to be due to the magneto calipers being misaligned.Â ','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4920,'One Fluid Ounce of Prevention','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'The alchemical solution that I\'ve made with the help of Buildmaster Angor should prevent our tents and encampment from going up in smoke when the battle begins. It\'s a strong mixture that ought to resist most of the magic that the wyrms might throw.',0,'The tents have been properly treated with our alchemical solution.Â ','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4921,'Out of Sight, Out of Mind','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Plex has given me the materials I\'ll need for the invisibility cloaks she needs. It\'s a tough job, but I need to give her as much cloak time as possible. Time to get to work.',0,'The invisibility cloaks are complete! They should last even longer than I first estimated.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4922,'Playing With Toys','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Denstarin has given me leave to install and test the upgraded ballista mechanisms.Â ',0,'After testing the ballistae, it looks like the existing torsion springs have been badly corroded. This is very odd considering all the parts are basically brand new. Denstarin and I will suss out a plan to figure out why this is happening.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4923,'Proving Them Wrong','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'The Commander has given me leave to see what I can do about the equipment situation for the soldiers here. Their equipment isn\'t bad, per se, but it\'s definitely not appropriate for the battle that they plan on engaging. I aim to make sure that we\'ve done absolutely everything we can to ensure our success.',0,'I\'ve drastically increased the New Combine\'s chances of winning this battle. I\'ve made it plain that Quartermaster Fahris has not served his post well, and I hope that he gets what\'s coming to him.Â ','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4924,'Questions for the Quartermaster','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Denstarin recommended that I seek out and chat with the Quartermaster. It seems he may be shirking his duties, and I might be able to lend a hand.',0,'I\'ve talked with Quartermaster Fahris, and left unimpressed. He says he has things under control though. Maybe I should see how the soldiers feel about him','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4925,'Ratcheting Up the Danger','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Supply Master Grant has tasked me with the delivery of the ballista mechanisms we worked on at the supply camp. The delivery is late, and the previous team met their end. Let\'s hope that I don\'t meet the same fate. I should head on up to the main New Combine camp.',0,'I\'ve delivered the components to Denstarin, the main camp\'s siegemaster. He was both surprised and pleased to finally have them.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4926,'Searching for an Answer','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Yeppa, one of the othmir that ran off in search of their homeland, has discovered that his homeland is not what it was. Those that lived here have died and risen as the undead, and now attack Yeppa and his contingent relentlessly. Though he is badly outmatched, he will not leave until he has given his brethren the peace that they deserve. We need to figure out what has scourged the land like this, and find a way to put the undead othmir to rest, permanently. To that end, I\'m going to make a detector that should point me in the direction of a solution.',0,'I\'ve found the source of the corruption - the giant bones that rise out of the ground. Every othmir structure seems made from them. This does not bode well...','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4927,'Searching for Clarity','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'After talking with the Quartermaster, I felt it was necessary to get some testimony from the soldiers themselves.Â ',0,'After talking with one of the soldiers it seems that morale is at an all-time low, almost purely because of the Quartermaster\'s inability to see the big picture. I need to convince him to change his perspective, or failing that, will have to go up the chain of command to find someone who will listen.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4928,'Seeing is Believing','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Plex needs some spotting glasses that she can use in the field. The hope is to have something that will give her enough knowledge of what she\'s getting into before committing her forces. I\'ve come up with a recipe that will serve, but I\'ll need to see if there\'s anyone around here who has lenses I can use - they\'ll take too long to machine myself. Hopefully there\'s a tinkerer around camp that can help me out. Once I have those, putting together the device should be a simple trick.',0,'The spotting glasses are complete. I\'ve given them to Plex, and am ready for the last thing on her list.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4929,'Sieging the Opportunity','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Taking a look at the siege components, I noticed some improvements that could be made. With Grant\'s leave, I\'m going to hopefully increase the energy output of them with a little bit of tinkering.',0,'I\'ve finished making my improvements to the siege components. I think Grant will be pleased.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4930,'Captain Overboard?','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'One of the Far Seas Trading Company crew said Captain Ethan wanted to talk to me, but that he\'d gone off to investigate something happening at the druid rings. I\'ll see if I can investigate further.',0,'I found Captain Ethan in a place called the Vesspyr Isles, an area of Ethernere that seems to be filled with dragons. I was able to help him free his flying mount, as well as assisting the Far Seas traders in learning more about the area.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4931,'Construct Deconstruction','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Jeremy has a plan to learn more about the region by planting recording devices in the Daar sentinel constructs around Daarspire, so that he can get recordings of everything that happens within earshot of the sentinels. This should be invaluable in helping the Far Seas Trading Company study the area.',0,'I assisted Jeremy by planting recording devices in the sentinel constructs around Daarspire isle. The recordings should help the Far Seas Trading Company learn more about what\'s happening in the region.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4932,'Far Seas Trading: Botanical Divergence','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Ethan would like to get this week\'s report from Claudia on the flora of Ethernere.',0,'I assisted Ethan in getting this week\'s update on Claudia\'s study of Ethernere flora.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4933,'Far Seas Trading: Fishing Up Fauna','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Ethan would like to get this week\'s report on the wildlife of Ethernere that Kate has been studying.',0,'I assisted Ethan in getting Kate\'s latest report on the wildlife of Ethernere.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4934,'Far Seas Trading: Reporting Home','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Ethan needs to send an update report back to headquarters and has asked me to get the latest status updates from his crew in Ethernere.',0,'I assisted Ethan in compiling and delivering the latest status report to headquarters.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4935,'Far Seas Trading: Researching the Recordings','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Ethan would like me to ask Jeremy for the latest information gathered from the recording devices we placed in the Daar sentinels.',0,'I assisted Ethan and Jeremy in getting the latest recordings from the recording devices we placed in the Daar sentinels.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4936,'Focused Fire','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Vanesta would like me to assist by crafting some new focus crystals to help the Wayward defenders.',0,'I assisted Vanesta with her daily work helping the Wayward defenders.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4937,'Herbs and Spirits','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Vanesta needs fresh bark, leaves, and berries to help the Wayward defenders.Â ',0,'I assisted Vanesta with her daily work helping the Wayward defenders.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4938,'Tonic for the Soul','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Vanesta would like me to help her by brewing up some barrels of healing tonic to help the Wayward defenders.',0,'I assisted Vanesta with her daily work helping the Wayward defenders.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4939,'Where Are All The Clean Bedrolls?','Tradeskill','Unknown',95,95,'Vanesta needs me to craft some clean bedrolls to keep the injured Wayward defenders clean and comfortable while they recover.',0,'I assisted Vanesta with her daily work helping the Wayward defenders.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4940,'A Missing Crewman','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Captain Ethan from the Far Seas Trading Company Supply Division has requested my assistance to find his missing second in command, Quartermaster Roberta Robbins.',0,'I made my way back to the Isle of Refuge. There is no sign of Quartermaster Robbins so far, and there has clearly been some magical catastrophe recently. I will continue to investigate the area to learn more.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4941,'D.I.R.T.Y. Business','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I\'m still puzzled what\'s happening on the island and if Gnorbert won\'t tell me, I\'ll investigate for myself!',0,'I investigated the excavation site and found what is unmistakably an artifact of Shissar origin! When confronted, Gnorbert confessed that the Far Seas Trading Company shut down access to the island and hired his crew to search for valuable artifacts when they suspected there might be something of value here.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4942,'D.I.R.T.Y. Explosives','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The dig site may also have been affected by whatever happened to the tower. I offered to check if anybody there needs help.',0,'I was able to remove the rubble trapping Gnorbert but he\'s still too injured to move.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4943,'D.I.R.T.Y. News','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Gnorbert is packing up the remaining equipment and will return to the D.I.R.T.Y. encampment in Drednever. He asked me to deliver his final report.',0,'It appears the Far Seas Trading Company deliberately shut off access to the Isle of Refuge while they hired an excavation team to search for relics, which appear to be related to shissar in some way. I have delivered Gnorbert\'s last report to Skrit, another crewmember sent by Captain Ethan to assist.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4944,'D.I.R.T.Y. Work','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I offered to find some healing help for Gnorbert.',0,'I made some healing salve infused bandages and brought them back to help Gnorbert.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4945,'Northward Bound','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Skrit found no news of Robbins, but has learned there are three more islands to the north we can check. She asked if I could leave the pygmy furnishings I made at her tent on the Isle of Refuge, then meet her at the largest of the three to continue the search.',0,'I arrived at Kithicor Island in the Phantom Sea to meet with Skrit again, and found her gravely injured!','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4946,'Repairing the Records','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Skrit has given me a recipe for restoring damaged scrolls and asked me to try and salvage what I can from the damaged notes I gathered.',0,'I restored the notes I found at the tower and dig site, and returned the information to Skrit. The notes mention that the Far Seas traders became suspicious there might be something valuable on the island after the dragon Darathar was so interested in the region. They appear to have found something valuable very recently.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4947,'Scampering to Investigate','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'It seems Duke Jaesten Ferrin, leader of the Far Seas Trading Company, has been secretive and untrusting of late, even to the Far Seas Trading Company\'s own Supply Division. I have agreed to help Skrit learn more of what was happening on the Isle of Refuge.',0,'I gathered all the damaged notes I could find from the area in hopes we can learn more about what happened here.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4948,'Taking Stock of Strangeness','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Skrit has asked me to catalog the affected flora and fauna around the ruined tower.',0,'I catalogued the affected flora and fauna and brought the information back to Skrit.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4949,'Village of Dshinn','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Skrit learned that Robbins was seen heading north. We agreed to continue the search at the island of South Dshinn, to the northeast of the Isle of Refuge.',0,'I met with Skrit and updated her on progress so far.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4950,'In a Pickle','Tradeskill','Unknown',0,0,'',0,'','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4951,'Shopping List','Tradeskill','Unknown',0,0,'',0,'','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4952,'Better Baricades','Tradeskill','Unknown',0,0,'',0,'','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4953,'A Call for Expertise','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I received a message from Trade Liaison Wells, asking me to meet him in person to assist with a matter of some concern to the city.',0,'Trade Liaison Wells showed me a mysterious artifact and a blank codex, and explained the items had been brought by from the Tranquil Sea. The city considers it a high priority to learn their origins and significance, and knowing my expertise in investigating odd crafting matters, Wells requested my assistance to identify the items. My initial findings suggest they originated in Kunark.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4954,'Armament Improvisation','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Quartermaster Robbins asked me to take inventory of the supplies left, and try to come up with a recipe for weapons we could make with what remains.',0,'I came up with a recipe for some glaive-like weapons that could be made using what supplies remain, and gave the recipe to Quartermaster Robbins.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4955,'Borrowed Knowledge','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The Duality confirmed the items look like shissar artifacts, and agreed to open a portal to Mayong Mistmoore\'s research chamber. Mistmoore is known to have been researching and collecting shissar artifacts lately, and may have more details on these items.',0,'Thanks to the portal opened by the Duality, I was able to transcribe copies of Mayong Mistmoore\'s research notes on shissar artifacts and technology. I will work with the Duality to further research these items.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4956,'Final Assessment','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The Duality has identified the codex, and planned some tests to perform on the other artifact that may help to reveal its origin and purpose.',0,'With the Duality\'s help, I learned that the blank codex was a tome containing powerful teleportation spells, and the other artifact appears to be something to do with transferring magical energy. Both appear to be from around the time of Ssraeshza. I rushed this information back to Trade Liaison Wells, who will update the city\'s representatives and warn them that powerful teleportation spells may be in someone\'s possession.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4957,'Highhold Ho','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Skrit is returning to the Tranquil Sea to heal up, and has asked me to proceed to the Far Seas Trading Company\'s headquarters in Castle Highhold, where I may be able to get help finding Quartermaster Robbins.',0,'Skrit sent me to Castle Highhold, the Far Seas Trading Company\'s headquarters. I found the castle is under attack, and Quartermaster Robbins has been busy here helping the defenders protect the castle.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4958,'Return to Refuge','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Quartermaster Robbins intends to stay here and assist the defenders while improving relations with Keep Master Yonette. She asked me to let Skrit and Captain Ethan know she is okay, and to bring news of the situation here.',0,'I returned to the Isle of Refuge and updated Skrit on the situation at Castle Highhold. Quartermaster Both Skrit and Robbins may need further help in the future.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4959,'Reviving the Ratonga','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I need to make a healing poultice for Skrit using the Tunarian trumpetleaf plants I gathered in the Blessed Knoll.',0,'The Tunare-blessed healing poultice appears to have saved Skrit. She\'ll need some time to recover, but she\'ll live.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4960,'Scale of Research','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I agreed to continue investigating the mysterious artifacts, and since they appear to have originated in Kunark, I will start by consulting some experts there.',0,'I spoke to a researcher in Teren\'s Grasp, who confirmed the artifacts are not iksar in origin but may be shissar. He directed me to consult the most respected expert on the shissar, the being known as the Duality. I located the Duality\'s sanctum in Odus and he agreed to help my investigations further.Â ','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4961,'Spiteweed Snare','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Quartermaster Robbins suggested I gather some young spiteweed from the coastal areas of Kithicor forest, and use it to concoct a potent brew to slow our enemies',0,'I gathered young spiteweed according to Quartermaster Robbins\' instructions, and used it to brew a potent potion that will even slow the undead.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4962,'Unfriendly Forest','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Skrit seems to be gravely injured, I need to find help.',0,'One of the far seas mariners told me where to find some plants with great healing properties at a site that had been blessed by Tunare. I\'ve brought some back to make a healing poultice for Skrit.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4963,'Blessed Healing','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Several of the defenders have been injured recently, and Quartermaster Robbins would like me to gather Tunarian trumpetleaf from the Blessed Knoll and make some healing poultices for them.',0,'I crafted more healing poultices and brought them to the injured defenders at Castle Highhold.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4964,'Feeling Defensive','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Arms Master Ryan needs more barricades to protect the defenders. Quartermaster Robbins has asked me to craft a new batch and deliver them to him.',0,'I created and delivered the barricades to Arms Master Ryan to protect the defenders at Castle Highhold.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4965,'Fruitful Foraging','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The Far Seas traders constantly need supplies of fresh fruit and vegetables to sustain the encampment. Skrit would like me to harvest some freshly picked hylocereus fruit, Kith pepper, and/or sulfur fruit to replenish the stores.',0,'I assisted Skrit by replenishing the encampment\'s fresh fruit and vegetable stocks.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4966,'Grim Running','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Skrit would like me to use a tinkered snare to stun one of the grimling runners who are sometimes seen spying on the dig site. She wants to check what they are carrying back and forth, in case there are any clues to their origin or intention.',0,'I assisted Skrit by stunning and searching one of the grimling runners to see what he was carrying back and forth.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4967,'Legendary Pepper','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The Isle of Refuge is the only known place in Norrath where the piperacea plant grows. Pepper from this plant is very valuable for trade, and Skrit would appreciate my assistance in restocking her supplies.',0,'I assisted Skrit by gathering some pepper for the Far Seas Trading Company to use for trade.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4968,'Salve Supplies','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The Far Seas encampment is always in need of healing as the area is still quite dangerous. The dogwood shrubs that grow around the encampment and on the hills above have strong healing properties and make an excellent healing salve.',0,'I assisted Skrit by creating some healing salve to keep the Far Seas encampment well supplied to treat injuries.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4969,'Sampling the Danger','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Skrit wants to keep an eye on the state of the magical corruption around the ruins of Malvonicus\' tower. She\'d like me to gather soil samples. By examining the magical residue each week, she may be able to learn more about the cause, and whether the situation is improving or getting worse.',0,'I assisted Skrit by gathering soil samples to allow her to continue monitoring the status of the magical residue at the tower.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4970,'Small Arms for Small Arms','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The pygmies report being attacked recently by aggressive lizard-like creatures. They\'ve asked to trade for some weapons they can use to defend their village.',0,'I assisted Skrit by forging some pygmy-sized weapons that she can use for trade to the pygmies.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4971,'Sour Tooth','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Skrit has asked if I can make some more pickles for trade with the pygmies.',0,'I assisted Skrit by cooking up more pickles for future trade with the pygmies.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4972,'Weapon Crates Restock','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The Castle Highhold defenders are running low on spare weapons. Quartermaster Robbins would like me to craft some more at the forge, then refill the weapons racks.',0,'I restocked the weapons racks for the Castle Highhold defenders.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4973,'Weapons with Benefits','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Quartermaster Robbins thinks we can improve the effectiveness of the defenders\' weapons. She has asked me to make some spiteweed brew and apply it to the defenders\' spare swords.',0,'I created fresh spiteweed brew and applied it to the defenders\' swords to improve their effectiveness in battle.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4974,'Assay of Origin','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Ethan asked me to speak with Trader Cylianna who\'s brought back some of the elemental remains.',0,'I found that the &quot;elementals&quot; actually have tinkered mechanisms within. With Trader Cylianna\'s help, I determined that the metal does not correspond to any of the common ores we\'re familiar with.Â ','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4975,'Attuning the Portal','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Brumley thinks with my knowledge of the world above, I could help them attune the small tinkered portal that was used to try and send a message to Kaladim. This should make it possible to create a permanent, two-way portal, which might make it possible for more aid to reach Maldura.',0,'I created the attunement device, and have given it to Brumley to install in the portal, which is outside the city in Thalumbra, not too far from the entry to city. This should permanently allow two-way access between Maldura and the world above.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4976,'Containing the Stone','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'According to my research, if a magical stone is set in metal that\'s empowered with the same type of magic as the stone it holds, it should be possible to attune the container so it hides the power of the stone within. I can do the forge work, but I\'ll need the help of the glaufaye for the magic.',0,'With the help of the glaufaye, I created an empowered censer in which to place the chaos stone fragments to conceal their power from prying eyes. Unfortunately, before I could bring the censer back to Brytthel, some dark elves disguised as guards stole the stone from the Queen\'s crown! Brytthel will investigate ways to retrieve it and told me to keep the censer for now.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4977,'Fire Striker','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Tinkersmith\'s latest invention idea is a hammer that throws explosive darts. Sounds a little crazy to me, but I agreed to help him put it together.',0,'I assisted Tinkersmith by gathering the necessary supplies and assembling the explosive hammer prototype according to his blueprints.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4978,'For Your Eyes Only','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Charles Q Tinkersmith is ready for me to assemble the prototype of the powered viewfinder. He seems sure that this will establish the reputation of his new research facility.',0,'I assembled the powered viewfinder prototype and Tinkersmith asked me to deliver it to the Grand Artificer, but a gnemlin thug knocked me out and stole the prototype! When I returned with the bad news, Tinkersmith seemed only excited that the thief had mentioned someone called Black Bolt. It seems he believes Black Bolt\'s approval might actually be advantageous to him, although I have doubts about the character of his potential new patron.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4979,'Fuels Are Forever','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Tinkersmith continues his ambitious plans to found a new research branch for gnemlin research. He\'s working on a powered viewfinder prototype and needs some liquid fuel, which he believes I can make if I obtain the necessary ingredients.',0,'I ventured into the District of Ash and obtained a powerful solvent, some coal, and also a spare gear for Tinkersmith\'s powered viewfinder prototype. I was able to use the high pressure steam tank to convert the coal and solvent into a very potent liquid fuel.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4980,'Into the Unknown','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The Duality believes he has enough information now to open a portal that will lead to the origin location of the mysterious ore ... wherever that may be. It sounds as if it may be from Maldura, but there\'s only one way to find out for sure!',0,'I assisted the Duality in opening a portal leading to the origin of the mysterious ore. I entered the portal ... now it\'s time to find out if our theories are correct!','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4981,'Menace in the Mine','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'After I bandaged Brytthel, she promised to tell me more of what\'s going on, but first asked me to bring news of her injury in the mines to someone called Brumley Langboom in the city. She gave me her signet ring so the guards will know I can be trusted, and told me to meet her in the city later if I want to know more.',0,'Brumley was alarmed to hear that Brytthel had been injured at the mine, and he immediately asked me to return there to scan the mine with a device he gave me. The device lit up as bright as a Frostfell tree, which Brumley says is not a good sign and means something called &quot;immolated&quot; are present in the mine.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4982,'Monitor Malfunction','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Brumley reported some strange readings from one of the monitoring devices I placed earlier. He asked me to take a look and make sure it\'s not malfunctioning.',0,'I checked on the monitoring device and didn\'t find any immolated present, but I did find the bodies of two dead dhalgar citizens. Brumley is extremely concerned and has asked me to tell Brytthel immediately.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4983,'Monitoring the Situation','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Brumley suggested placing a monitoring device near each of the areas where the immolated are known to be, to alert him to any unusual activity. Unfortunately he\'s run out of supplies ... so he asked if I could make the gadgets.',0,'I made and placed some monitoring devices near the locations of the immolated, so Brumley will be alerted to any unusual activity.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4984,'More Ore of Yore','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Forgemaster Gert confirmed that the coldain were not able to bring any ore samples with them during their migration to Velious, but she suggested speaking to the Lorekeepers in the library in case there is any information in the histories that might give a clue about the origin of the great hammer in Kaladim.',0,'I learned from the coldain historians that the great hammer of Kaladim was a gift from the ancient underground city of Maldura. Since the hammer\'s ore matched the metal from the &quot;elemental&quot; mechanisms, they presumably originate in the same place. It seems my best lead points me to somewhere in the Underfoot ...Â ','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4985,'Ore of Yore','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I need to learn more about the origin of the metal from the &quot;elementals&quot; that have appeared around Norrath lately. The metal is no ore commonly in use these days. Perhaps the dwarves have more records on unusual ores that might help.',0,'With the assistance of Dror, we confirmed the metal from the elementals matches the metal from the great hammer in Kaladim. But that metal is very old, and its origin no longer in the dwarves\' records.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4986,'Researching a Solution','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Brytthel is concerned that the stone in the Queen\'s crown - her responsibility to safeguard - may be what\'s attracting all the recent attacks. I asked if there is any way to hide its power, but she\'s unsure. She says it and another similar stone originally came from the glaufaye who live in the forest outside, so I\'m going to ask them if they know of any way to hide these powerful items.',0,'I searched the Maldura library for references to the ancient arts of the dhalgar, and found some references that seemed relevant. With a little work, I combined the information into a recipe for a censer that might conceal the power of the stones from prying eyes.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4987,'Scanning the Seals','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Brumley says he had believed the immolated, which are apparently some kind of wight-like creature, were sealed up in areas of the city. Now he\'s alarmed they\'ve found a way to escape, and he\'s asked me to help check the city is still secure.',0,'I placed more scanning devices in the areas of Maldura that Brumley said were sealed off to contain the immolated. Happily, they didn\'t light up like the one outside, so the seals within Maldura appear to be holding.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4988,'Scuttling to Safety','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Charles Q Tinkersmith is trying to establish a special branch for further development of gnemlin research. He is working on some reinforced armor and needs help obtaining beetle scales for the construction.',0,'I used Tinkersmith\'s blueprint to make a trap and was able to bring him an armored scuttler beetle for his reinforced armor research.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4989,'Stranger in Distress','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I arrived in what appears to be an old mine tunnel, and discovered a very unusual looking stranger who appears to be very badly injured.Â ',0,'I helped the injured stranger by bandaging her up, and it looks as if she\'ll live now. Her name is Brytthel, she is a type of dwarf called a dhalgar, and she has promised to tell me more if I look her up once she\'s back in the nearby city. In the mean time she asked my help to inform someone called Brumley Longboom about what happened here.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4990,'Subtunarian Subterfuge','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Using the roekillik illusion, I need to convince the elder roekillik that I\'m a respectful roekillik youth who wishes to learn more about our history.',0,'I convinced the roekillik elder that I was a young roekillik seeking to learn more about our history, and he sketched out for me a guide to where he remembered the dwarves\' ancient trade routes and cities could be found.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4991,'The Man with the Tinkered Eye','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Charles Q Tinkersmith continues his attempts to establish a special research branch for gnemlin research. Unfortunately, all his prototypes were left behind when his research lab was overtaken by the immolated. He\'s asked me to go in and retrieve some prototype eyepieces and spare lenses.',0,'I returned to the remains of the research lab and retrieved the box of spare lenses, as well as the prototype eyepieces. Tinkerfest didn\'t mention I\'d actually have to remove them from their former testers, but I suppose they had no further use for them.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4992,'Underfoot Defender','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The Duality did recall the dwarves had underground cities and trade routes, and may be able to assist me in gathering more details.',0,'The Duality gave me a copy of an old map showing me the Mines of Moradhim, and assisted me in creating a roekillik illusion which allowed me to speak to a roekillik elder.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4993,'You Only Test Twice','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I\'m pretty sure Tinkersmith was planning to test the explosive hammer prototype on me, but when I raised the question he suggested constructing an armored clockwork test target. This seems like something I can assist with.',0,'Unfortunately, the explosive hammer prototype backfired and exploded damaging me as well as destroying the clockwork, meaning neither the hammer nor the armor plating are working quite yet.Â ','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4994,'A Finding Charm','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Glibnox has enchanted the charm for finding lost things, and it\'s time for me to use it!',0,'The charm seems to have found a lost person, but not the ones I\'m looking for; I found a lost injured goblin instead!','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4995,'An Urgent Call','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I received an unexpected message from Brytthel in Maldura asking me to meet her on a matter of highest urgency.',0,'Brytthel and Queen Alwenielle explained that the enchantment spells hiding the Arcanna\'se spire are fading as the glaufaye become mortal once again, and they have come up with a plan to create a decoy chaos stone to replace the one hidden in the spire. My skills are needed to craft the imitation stone.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4996,'Bone Collecting','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Glibnox offered to help me find a way to track the iksar using a scrying spell made from chokidai bones. First, I need to collect the bones.',0,'I collected the chokidai bones and returned to Glibnox for the spell.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4997,'Borrowing From The Dead','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The goblins of Broken Toe clan will not help me until I earn their trust. Irontooth would appreciate my help obtaining some armor upgrades for the goblin fighters.Â ',0,'I helped repair some of the rusty old armor in the area so the goblins can make use of it.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4998,'Choose the Slug Life','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Elder Lyraquel wants me to gather some slugs from Twark and transplant them to a new home in the Nye\'Caelona gardens, where they can breed and keep the borer beetles under control',0,'The Cae\'dal elves of Nye\'Caelona seem to have made a beginner\'s mistake in ecology. When they eliminated a creature they thought was unappealing from their gardens, they upset the ecological balance and the borer beetles were able to spread out of control. The reintroduction of the slugs should eventually get the borer beetle population under control once again.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(4999,'Deeper Disguise','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I tricked Trooper Selisk with a disguise and asked about the adventurers they found on the beach. He says I\'ll need to ask Trooper Sokszar in the caves.',0,'I spoke to Trooper Sokszar but unfortunately she reported the adventurers have already moved on. On the bright side, it sounds as if the chaos stone is still safely in their possession.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5000,'Drop Your Weapon','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The goblins of Broken Toe clan will not help me until I earn their trust. Irontooth wants to replenish the goblins\' weapon supply.',0,'I was able to collect some abandoned old weapons and repair them for the goblins.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5001,'Dying of Bore-dom','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Lyraquel explained the elves\' gardens have a serious pest problem with Borer Beetles. They have been trying various solutions to exterminate the beetles but she has doubts, and has asked me to go and check.',0,'I dug up a typharush plant and although I saw no signs of adult borer beetles, there were still larvae in the soil underground.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5002,'Feeling Crabby','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Kreeg could use my crafting skills to help him make some crab traps.',0,'I foraged up supplies and crafted some crab traps for Kreeg.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5003,'Figurine the Profits','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I met an iksar near the pass who is looking for valuable artifacts that may have been buried in the rubble. She says she\'s one figurine short of a set and will pay well if I chance to find it.',0,'I found the figurine the iksar was missing and returned it to her for a profit.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5004,'Forging Onwards','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Elanluelle has given me instructions on how to create an imitation chaos stone using enchanted blushing umbrite provided by Queen Alwenielle, and the magic-infused pollen of the zeabuds growing near the village. I\'m to bring the imitation stone back to Alwenielle as soon as possible.',0,'I created the imitation stone and delivered it to Queen Alwenielle. Unfortunately, while I was delivering the news to Elanluelle, the queen felt her spell start slipping. She entered the Arcanna\'se spire ahead of us with a group of adventurers in hopes of protecting the stone, and left a note asking me to follow.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5005,'Gathering Shinies','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Vhesh seems to enjoy shiny things, so if I find some for him, perhaps he\'ll be a little more inclined to help me find the adventurers he saw.',0,'I gathered some sand shillings from the beach and polished them bright and shiny for Vhesh\'s enjoyment.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5006,'Getting Hooked','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'A strange goblin on the beach seems to need some help with his fishing.',0,'A strange goblin on the beach seems to be trying fairly unsuccessfully to catch fish. In the interests of earning the trust of the goblins, I offered to help him by making some fish hooks.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5007,'Gone Astray','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'It appears my disguise is so effective that Trooper Sokszar believes I\'m the duty captain, and expects me to take care of a stray sokokar problem. Since I don\'t want them to realize I\'m not really one of them, I guess I\'m going to catch a sokokar.',0,'I caught a stray sokokar and delivered it to Chef Zharss. It appears the crusaders have a very unforgiving way of teaching sokokars not to stray.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5008,'Googlow Juice','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The goblins of Broken Toe clan will not help me until I earn their trust. Rumbletum would like to get some fresh googlow juice to keep the goblin warriors healthy.',0,'I gathered goocap mushrooms and made some fresh googlow juice for the goblins.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5009,'Hung Out To Dry','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Kreeg may not have caught any fish yet, but he wants to be sure he\'ll have somewhere to hang them when he does.',0,'I foraged up some supplies and crafted a drying rack for Kreeg to hang the fish on.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5010,'If The Bones Fit','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The goblins of Broken Toe clan will not help me until I earn their trust. Brappa could use a hand making totems to protect the troops.',0,'I helped Brappa make some protective totems for the troops.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5011,'Into The Spire','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Queen Alwenielle left a note saying she\'s gone ahead of me into the Arcanna\'se spire with some adventurers, to forestall the Primordial Malice. I\'m to follow after as soon as possible.',0,'As soon as I entered the Arcanna\'se spire it was clear the Primordial Malice had discovered the entry. I was able to locate the queen and free her from her captors. She explained she was able to teleport the adventurers to safety with the chaos stone, and asked me to follow after to help if I can. I have arrived in Obulus Frontier ... now to find the others if I can!','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5012,'Keep The Home Fires Burning','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The goblins of Broken Toe clan will not help me until I earn their trust. Rumbletum is running low on firewood for cooking the goblins food, and needs some more.',0,'I gathered plenty of wood for the goblins\' cooking needs.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5013,'Live Bait','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Kreeg needs some bait for his fish hooks. I can use some of the crab meat to lure out some wriggling crawlers that would tempt any fish.',0,'I caught plenty of wriggling crawlers for Kreeg to use as bait, and he\'s very well pleased with my help. I trust my assistance has helped earn the trust of this strange goblin clan.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5014,'Losers, Weepers','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Vhesh knows a charm for finding lost things, which he thinks might work to find the adventurers who were taken away. He\'s told me what I need to do to make it.',0,'I crafted the charm as Vhesh described. There is just one final step required.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5015,'Mission of Mercy','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I agreed to deliver a healing potion to the injured goblin.',0,'I helped heal the injured goblin so he can return to the clan.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5016,'Not Dead Yet','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I awoke on the beach and met a strange goblin who seems to think I am dead, or possibly a vampire. Apparently there are some plants growing around these cliffs that vampires dislike, so I\'ll bring back a handful to prove to the goblin that I\'m not undead.',0,'I gathered some of the smelly shrubs and brought them back to the goblin Vhesh, who still seems somewhat confused about the status of my mortality, but possibly open to persuasion.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5017,'Process of Elimination','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Elder Lyraquel has asked me to bring her samples of plant, animal, and fungal matter from Twark so she can see if there is anything different that might be discouraging the borer beetles',0,'I brought samples of plant, animal, and fungal matter from Twark for Elder Lyraquel to examine. While the plant and fungal samples looked similar to those in Nye\'Caelona, the animals I sampled - forest slugs - were eliminated from the Nye\'Caelona gardens shortly before the borer beetle infestation began.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5018,'Requesting Blessing','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Vhesh has helped me make a charm for finding lost things. I just need to get the soothsayer Glibnox to enchant it.',0,'I found the soothsayer Glibnox among the goblins. He agreed to enchant the charm for me while I helped him with a few tasks.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5019,'Scrying Eyes','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Glibnox has given me instructions on how to assemble and use the scrying bones to find the iksar who took the adventurers from the beach.',0,'I used the scrying bones and they led me to an encampment of iksar.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5020,'Sickly-Brews for Stabby-Sticks','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The goblins of Broken Toe clan will not help me until I earn their trust. Brappa could use a hand making poisons for the goblins\' weapons.',0,'I helped Brappa make some poisons for the goblins\' weapons.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5021,'Smoothy-Stones for Stabby-Sticks','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The goblins of Broken Toe clan will not help me until I earn their trust. Irontooth needs some sharpening stones to keep their weapons in top condition.',0,'I gathered some smooth stones for Irontooth to use as sharpening stones.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5022,'Soil and Trouble','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Elder Lyraquel doesn\'t understand why the borer beetles seem to plague Nye\'Caelona, but not other areas nearby such as Twark. She asked me to gather soil samples to see if there\'s a difference.',0,'I gathered soil samples from Nye\'Caelona and Twark and the samples confirmed borer beetles are not found in Twark.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5023,'Squirmy-Wormies for Grumbly-Bellies','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The goblins of Broken Toe clan will not help me until I earn their trust. Rumbletum would like my help gathering some delicious &quot;squirmy wormies&quot; to keep them fed.',0,'I collected plenty of worms from under the rocks and brought them back to feed the goblins.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5024,'Stacky-Racks for Stabby-Sticks','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The goblins of Broken Toe clan will not help me until I earn their trust. Brappa could use a hand making weapon racks for the camp.',0,'I helped Brappa by crafting some weapon racks for the goblins.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5025,'Stranger Friends','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Glibnox said a &quot;friend&quot; of mine who doesn\'t like eating slugs came by and headed towards Nye\'Caelona. I\'d better go see who it is.',0,'Brytthel has made her way out to the Obulus Frontier, and I found her getting acquainted with the Cae\'dal elves. While it seems the chaos stone is safe with the adventurers for the time being, we agreed to both listen for news that might lead us to the stone or give us a warning that Lanys T\'Vyl\'s forces might have located it.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5026,'Temple Visitor','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I\'ve finally earned the trust of the goblins of Broken Toe clan. Brappa said a goblin by the name of Greshdek did show up recently, and can likely be found in the temple of Nu\'roga, which I now have their permission to enter.',0,'I gained the trust of the Broken Toe Clan goblins and now have safe access to the temple of Nu\'roga.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5027,'The Final Blow','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Brytthel and I have agreed to be proactive and plan for the worst. We need to plan for the worst case scenario if Lanys T\'Vyl acquires the last of the Chaos Stones, by finding a way to create a weapon that has the power to defeat her. Apparently there is a legendary weaponsmith Dalnir who once lived in this region, and there may be a way to contact him still. My task is now to investigate this possibility and see if I can come up with a way to safeguard all our futures.',0,'I found a way to speak with the legendary weaponsmith Haggle Baron Dalnir, creator of the Greenmist khukri. From the information he provided, I was able to deduce a way to modify the relics in the Arcanna\'se spire so they can act as a conduit and channel the power of their respective gods into weapon of epic strength. Brytthel and Queen Alwenielle will be getting this information to the powerful adventurers who posses weapons of this quality, and we hope that together our efforts may create a weapon powerful enough to defeat Lanys T\'Vyl even at her most powerful.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5028,'The Gardens Are In Bloom','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The elves of Nye\'Caelona do not trust strangers. When I persisted in asking to earn their trust, Taelonar told me to deliver a message for him, to someone called Marqusal who awaits at the docks of Danak.',0,'It seems the spell of obfuscation was created by the elves of Nye\'Caelona, and the errand to Danak was apparently a ploy to get me to leave the area so I would forget Nye\'Caelona even exists. Little did they know the spell from Queen Alwenielle protects my memory, so Taelonar was very surprised to see my return. He directed me to talk to one of the elders and I explained my errand, and now have their grudging permission to remain so long as I tell no-one of their presence.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5029,'Always In Demand','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The Bloody Tooth goblins like to keep a full stock of healing brews, but it seems they\'re running low at the moment. I offered to help refill their supplies.',0,'I helped refill the Bloody Tooth goblins\' store of healing brew.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5030,'Blessing of Growf','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'It seems Growf is quite the gardening goblin. However, he\'s run out of fertilizer, and hopes I can help him obtain more.',0,'I helped Growf by gathering some fertilizer for his gardening.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5031,'Budding Progress','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The seed appears to have developed into a bud! And my former gathering goblin, now working as a gardening goblin, showed up in my home to check up on it and help out.',0,'The gardening goblin is glad to see the plant has reached bud stage, and advised me on how to help it grow.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5032,'Greener On The Other Side','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The goblins are trying to establish a trade relationship with the Cae\'dal elves in Nye\'Caelona. It seems the elves highly value the special blend of fertilizer created by the goblins, and wish to trade for it. I offered to help prepare and deliver some.',0,'I helped further trade relations between Twark and Nye\'Caelona by delivering some bags of the excellent fertilizer the Bloody Tooth goblin clan creates.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5033,'Guardian of Growf','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Now Growf is back in Twark, he seems eager to get back to work growing his plants. However, he\'s run out of pest repellent spray and could use some help making more.',0,'I helped Growf to make a pest repellent spray to protect his plants.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5034,'Home Sickness','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The plant is larger, but now appears sick! My goblin gardener advises me to take a soil sample to Growf and get his expert opinion.',0,'Growf was able to recommend some additional luclin rock in the soil, which I obtained and delivered. The plant appears better already.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5035,'Protector of Growf','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Growf seems very worried about the safety of his plants, and wants me to help him coat them with a repulsive substance that should guarantee nobody wants to get close to them, let alone steal them.',0,'I helped Growf protect his plants by collecting a disgusting, smelly substance for him to coat them with.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5036,'Pup Piper','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The Bloody Tooth goblins use chokidai hide to make the armor they wear. The hides of young pups work best, as the leather is not yet too thick and stiff to work with. I offered to help them catch some.',0,'I helped the Bloody Tooth goblin clan by catching chokidai pups.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5037,'Rabbit Repellent','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The goblins are trying to establish a trade relationship with the Cae\'dal elves in Nye\'Caelona. It seems the elves have noticed some of the local rabbits nibbling at unprotected seedlings in the garden, and wish to trade for some of Growf\'s rabbit repellent spray.',0,'I helped further trade relations between Twark and Nye\'Caelona by delivering some rabbit repellent spray to protect their seedlings.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5038,'Seeds of Growf','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Growf has heard that the elves to the east of Twark have strange and unique plants due to their skill with growing things. He\'s asked me to try and collect some seeds from their gardens, if I find myself in the area.',0,'I was able to collect some plant seeds from Nye\'Caelona for Growf.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5039,'Snacky Snacks','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The Bloody Tooth goblins\' food supplies are running low, so I offered to help refill their favorites.',0,'I crafted plenty of fresh food and drink for the goblins of Bloody Tooth clan to replenish their stores for the week.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5040,'The Gardening Goblin','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The plant is larger, and is now glowing! The gardening goblin says this means it\'s ripe, and I should check among the leaves.',0,'I helped confirm Growf\'s theory that the plant is able to produce rare harvests over time, as a reaction to the magical luclin rock in the soil. If I keep this plant in my house, I will be able to gather valuable harvests from it on a regular basis.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5041,'Thumpy Sticks','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The Bloody Tooth goblins need to remain armed and vigilant to protect their clan from the many threatening creatures in Obulus Frontier. I offered to help make some new &quot;thumpy sticks&quot; for their fighters.',0,'I helped the Bloody Tooth goblin clan by crafting some new weapons.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5042,'Tree of Growf','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Encouraged by Growf\'s persuasive moral arguments, I have decided to release my gathering goblin from servitude.Â ',0,'I crafted a fine container for the seed and have placed it in my home. My former goblin gatherer is overjoyed to be released from harvesting servitude, and has agreed to stop in and check on the seedling\'s progress in a day or two.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5043,'Twark Defender','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The previous batch of hide from chokidai pups has finished the tanning process and is ready to be crafted into leather armor for the goblins of The Bloody Tooth clan. I offered my assistance to create it.',0,'I helped the Bloody Tooth goblin clan by crafting sturdy new armor from the hide of chokidai pups.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5044,'Unlikely Saviors','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'The goblins are trying to establish a trade relationship with the Cae\'dal elves in Nye\'Caelona. It seems the elves have found the slugs are effective in keeping the borer beetles in check, and would like to trade for some more.',0,'I helped further trade relations between Twark and Nye\'Caelona by delivering some slugs for their gardens.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5045,'A Cure for Maldura','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Brumley has sent a request via Gwynvyn to let you know he could use your assistance on a weekly basis. Speak to him directly for the details.',0,'Brumley is apparently trying some curative magics in the District of Ash to see if they have any effect on the immolated. He sent me with a tinkered scanner to collect readings so they could look for any improvement.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5046,'Arming Maldura','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Gwynvyn coordinates the delivery of replacement equipment for the guards of Maldura on a weekly basis.',0,'Gwynvyn let me know the guards could use some replacement equipment, and I delivered it to Quartermaster Lysslyn.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5047,'Healing for Maldura','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Once a week, the healers of Maldura need to restock their supplies of healing salve-infused bandages. The supplies can be gathered just outside the city, and the bandages should be returned to the healers\' supply containers.',0,'I assisted the healers of Maldura by restocking their supplies of healing salve-infused bandages.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5048,'Malduran Medicine','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Once a week, Gwynvyn checks with the healers of Maldura to see if they need assistance in restocking their healing potions. They are often running short of something, and this week is no exception.',0,'Gwynvyn let me know the healers were short on potions, so I crafted some replacements and delivered them to healer Dalryl.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5049,'Malduran Mouths to Feed','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Once a week, Gwynvyn coordinates with local crafters to arrange for a special hot meal for all the hard-working Maldura guards, who often have to make do with cold rations during their long shifts.',0,'I cooked some delicious hot meals for the hard-working guards and delivered them to Quartermaster Lysslyn, who said the guards look forward to this treat every week.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5050,'Malduran Refills','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Once a week, Gwynvyn checks with the guards to find out what supplies they\'re running short of, and arranges for someone to deliver the extras they need.',0,'Gwynvyn gave me a load of equipment the guards had requested, and I delivered it to the Quartermaster\'s supply stores.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5051,'Monitoring Maldura','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Brumley has sent a request via Gwynvyn to let you know he could use your assistance on a weekly basis. Speak to him directly for the details.',0,'I helped Brumley by replacing the mana batteries of the monitors I placed earlier.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5052,'Restocking the Deepforge Depot','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Gwynvyn checked the Deepforge Founders\' supplies of harvestables and let me know what they need most this week.',0,'I gathered fresh harvests to restock the supplies of the Deepforge Founders.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5053,'Search and Rescue','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'I found a collection of goblin items around the pass in the hills. Perhaps these would have some value to the goblins.',0,'I finally earned the trust of the goblins of Nu\'roga and was able to locate Greshdek in the temple of Nu\'roga. The teleportation charm from Glibnox brought us safely back to Twark.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5054,'Time Is Short','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Queen Alwenielle contacted me within Arcanna\'se Spire to help me reach the relics of the dead gods. While she cannot grant me permanent immunity, she has cast a spell on me that will activate when I enter their demesnes and will allow me entry for a short time period only. I\'ll have to work quickly and be gone again before the spell wears off.',0,'Despite working against short time constraints, I managed to find and empower each of four relics of the dead gods whose icons were saved in Zou Kunnen\'s shard of magic. The relics are now ready to imbue an epic quality weapon with the power of the lost gods, which should create a weapon powerful enough to defeat even Lanys T\'Vyl.Â ','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5055,'The Plan of Growf','Tradeskill','Unknown',100,100,'Growf has somehow discovered that I have magical control over a goblin servant, whom I can order to gather harvested materials for me. He feels strongly that this is unethical servitude and has asked me to talk to my goblin servant to find out what he or she really wants.',0,'I spoke to my gathering goblin and discovered that she does not, in fact, enjoy working endlessly as a harvesting servant. In fact, she is interested in learning some of Growf\'s gardening skills and perhaps taking up adventuring as a profession in the future. I will need to think deeply on this.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5056,'Restoring Valor','Tradeskill','Unknown',0,0,'',0,'','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5057,'A Stitch in Time, Part I: Security Measures','Tradeskill','Unknown',110,110,'I\'ve met with Druzzil Ro, who explained that while the Tenets of Hate were defeated and the portal to Time was destroyed, the victory had a side effect - another gateway to the Plane of Time, built by Meldrath the Malignant, was damaged. Druzzil Ro and the other deities are concerned that it might allow another malevolent actor to enter the plane through the crack, which could have unthinkable consequences. She has asked that I enter the Plane of Innovation, and retrieve the plans Meldrath used to build his machine to Time.',0,'Although it took some ingenuity and fancy handiwork, I was able to bypass Meldrath\'s security and found my way into his workshop. I\'ve returned the plans to Varig Ro, who should be able to begin working on repairs.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5058,'A Stitch in Time, Part II: Lightning Strikes','Tradeskill','Unknown',110,110,'Varig Ro has Meldrath\'s plans to repair the gateway to Time, but needs help gathering the materials to do his job. In order to help him finish the work, I\'ve agreed to journey out to Bastion of Thunder to meet with Karana. Varig Ro needs a few rods of solidified lightning, and believes that the Rainkeeper can provide them for him.',0,'Unfortunately, Karana was focused on repairing the Bastion, and wasn\'t able to provide me with the materials that I needed. He did, however, order the storm giants to allow my passage so that I might craft the materials myself. Although it took me to all corners of Karana\'s keep, I was able to gather what I needed and create the rods of solidified lightning for Varig Ro.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5059,'A Stitch in Time, Part III: From Birth to Tombs','Tradeskill','Unknown',110,110,'In order to ensure that the portal to Time is locked forever, the deific powers of the pantheon must be brought together to seal the gateway shut. While several of the gods have already committed a piece of their power, others - including Solusek Ro and Bertoxxulous - have not. Solusek Ro has retreated to consult with Fennin Ro following the destruction of the Molten Throne, and Bertoxxulous appears to have his own ends and will not respond to the requests. Thus, I\'ve been asked to enter their planes and gather the necessary energies to create the seals that are needed.',0,'That was quite the journey! I witnessed the rebirth of the great phoenix Arlyxir, and from his emergence, I was able to absorb the burning power needed to charge the first seal. Empowering the second seal required digging through the Crypt of Decay, and locating the latent energies of the Plaguebringer. I was able to gather what I needed, however, and we now have two of the seals we would otherwise be missing.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5060,'A Stitch in Time, Part IV: A Favor of Love','Tradeskill','Unknown',110,110,'The repairs to the Time portal should be nearly complete, however one crucial part is missing - the essence of Hate. In order to properly seal the gate, Varig Ro will need a way to gather the needed essence of Hate. He doesn\'t have an idea of how to do that, so he has asked that I consult with Druzzil Ro and see if she might have a solution.',0,'To my surprise, and likely, the surprise of everyone around me, Innoruuk wasn\'t completely destroyed by the actions of Lanys T\'Vyl- he had been reduced to a mortal form, albeit a nearly mindless one. Druzzil Ro believes there may be a way to return him to his plane, but it required Varig Ro to forge the proper item - something he was not willing to do, given his apparent respect for Erollisi Marr. In another surprise turn, Erollisi gave her blessing to attempt the process, effectively giving permission to return one of her mortal enemies to his stature.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5061,'A Stitch in Time, Part V: Sealed With Hate','Tradeskill','Unknown',110,110,'With Erollisi Marr\'s blessing, Varig has agreed to make a device to initiate apotheosis on the mortal form of Innoruuk, but needs the latent shards of his power. It\'s likely these were left when Lanys was destroyed in the Molten Throne, and although the Fire Tyrant warned mortals to never return, necessity means that I will have to do so anyway. The portal to Time must be sealed, and I will have to put myself in harm\'s way to do so.',0,'Although the journey was long, fraught with danger, and required much of me and my skills, I was able to help Varig and Druzzil Ro, and ultimately, the pantheon as a whole, finally seal Meldrath\'s machine and prevent any intrusion into the Plane of Time. Perhaps now it will remain locked off to all - mortal or divine.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5062,'Piercing the Darkness: Carving A Legacy','Tradeskill','Unknown',110,110,'Head Scholar Nabihan, a senior Deepwater Circle researcher, has been charged with overseeing the creation and empowerment of Luclinite Propylons, required by the Duality. These powerful gating objects are based upon similar ones Al\'Kabor developed during the Age of Turmoil, but made of luclinite, and much bigger.',0,'Head Scholar Nabihan, a senior Deepwater Circle researcher, appreciated my assistance with creating the challenging Luclinite Propylons, required by the Duality.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5063,'Piercing the Darkness: Monuments of Mythic Passage','Tradeskill','Unknown',110,110,'Head Scholar Nabihan has sent me to speak with Taith McJarun, a Deepwater Circle researcher working with the Duality, stationed near the Combine Spires at Teren\'s Grasp, in Kylong Plains.',0,'I spoke with Taith McJarun, a Deepwater Circle researcher working with the Duality, stationed near the Combine Spires at Teren\'s Grasp, in Kylong Plains.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5064,'Dynamist on the List','Tradeskill','Unknown',0,0,'',0,'','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5065,'Shoot for the Stars','Tradeskill','Unknown',0,0,'',0,'','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5066,'Bastion of Thunder - Storm Rider\'s Sash','Tradeskill','Unknown',115,115,'I should gather the correct items and craft the Storm Rider\'s Sash.',0,'I was able to successfully create a Storm Rider\'s Sash from the correct components, in the Bastion of Thunder.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5067,'Bastion of Thunder - Stormwatcher\'s Ring','Tradeskill','Unknown',115,115,'I should gather the correct items and craft the Stormwatcher\'s Ring.',0,'I was able to successfully create a Stormwatcher\'s Ring from the correct components, in the Bastion of Thunder.','Quests/MultipleZones/Empty.lua'),(5068,'Bastion of Thunder - Vial of Pure Rain','Tradeskill','Unknown',115,115,'I should gather the correct items and craft the Vial of Pure Rain.',0,'I was able to successfully create a Vial of Pure Rain from the correct compone